:h2 res=10022 x=right width=70%.Licence And Disclaimer
:p.
While older XFolder versions were "plain" freeware,
all XFolder versions since V0&per.80 and XWorkplace
too have been placed under the :hp2.GNU General Public Licence
(GPL):ehp2. Version 2&per. 
:p.
You can find the full text of the GPL in the plain-text
file :font facename='Courier' size=18x12.COPYING:font facename=default size=0x0. in the XWorkplace installation directory&per.
A formatted version of this document is available on
the :link reftype=hd res=10023.next page:elink. of this document&per. :hp2.
:p.
By installing XWorkplace on your system, you declare
your agreement to the terms and conditions of the GNU
General Public Licence, Version 2, as contained in the
file COPYING in the XWorkplace installation directory&per.:ehp2.

:p.
The GPL means more Legalese, but also :hp2.more rights:ehp2. for
you as a user and, if applicable, developer&per. The
most obvious change is that XWorkplace's source code
is also released&per. 
:p.
The following brief explanations are intended as an
introduction to the terms and conditions of the GPL
only&per. They are not part of the licence agreement,
for which only the terms and conditions in the :font facename='Courier' size=18x12.COPYING:font facename=default size=0x0.
file shall prevail&per. 
:ul compact.:li.
If you are an :hp2.XWorkplace user,:ehp2. not much has changed&per.
You may still use XWorkplace without any payment to
anyone&per. The GPL does not restrict you on this matter,
because it only imposes restrictions on distribution
and modification of software&per. However, there is
still :hp2.no warranty:ehp2. whatsoever&per. If XWorkplace ruins
your system and your work of the last 30 years is lost,
sorry&per. (This is not very probable though)&per. Refer
to the bottom of the :link reftype=hd res=10023.GPL:elink. for the detailed disclaimer&per.

.br
:li.
If you're a :hp2.distributor,:ehp2. you may still distribute the
whole XWorkplace package&per. However, the GPL will
probably require you to also distribute the complete
XWorkplace source code&per. Refer to the :link reftype=hd res=10023.GPL:elink. for details&per.

.br
:li.
If you're a :hp2.developer,:ehp2. you now have the source code,
which you may use and modify&per. However, if you base
your own software on XWorkplace's source code, the GPL
will most probably :hp2.require you to place your work under
the GPL also&per.:ehp2. This means that you cannot use the
sources if you don't publish all your sources also&per.

:p.
Even though the source code is published, all developers
retain the copyright to what they've written&per. 
:p.
The GPL deals with these issues extensively&per. Before
you use or modify any code parts of XWorkplace, make
sure you read the GPL thoroughly&per. If your software
is GPL'd also, :hp2.by all means feel free to use the code&per.:ehp2.
If you have any questions, feel free to contact the
developer's team&per. 
:eul.
:p.
And now&colon. have fun with XWorkplace! 
.br

