:font facename='Courier' size=18x12.xworkplace-user@yahoogroups&per.com:font facename=default size=0x0. is for XWorkplace
users&per. Use this address for public discussions about
XWorkplace if you don't understand the source code&per.
However, for bug reports, we kindly ask you to use the
bugtracker listed below&per. 
.br
:li.
:font facename='Courier' size=18x12.xworkplace-dev@yahoogroups&per.com:font facename=default size=0x0. is for messages related
to the source code&per. This is used by the developers
to communicate and can also be used by anyone else&per.

:eul.
:p.
However, please read through the :link reftype=hd res=10016."Frequently Asked Questions":elink.
section before contacting the developers; maybe you
will already find what you're looking for in there&per.

:p.
To :hp2.report bugs,:ehp2. the recommended way is to use the official
XWorkplace bugtracker at :link reftype=hd res=10149.http&colon.//xtracker&per.netlabs&per.org:elink.&per.
Create an account for yourself, and then you can file
bugs&per. :link reftype=hd res=10100.:font facename='Courier' size=18x12.
:p.
http&colon.//www&per.xworkplace&per.org:font facename=default size=0x0.:elink. is XWorkplace's
home page on the World Wide Web&per. Watch this space
for news, updates, and public downloads&per. 
:p.
A :hp2.public bug list:ehp2. is also maintained on that homepage&per.
:hp2.
:p.
Reporting bugs&per.:ehp2. Please include the following information
(the more, the better)&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
Please describe the situation in which the error occured
and whether it is reproduceable&per. 
.br
:li.
Include the :hp2.OS/2 version:ehp2. you are running (Warp 3 or
4, MCP/ACP/1/2, eComStation, including the fixpak level)&per.

.br
:li.
Include a list of :hp2.other PM or WPS enhancers:ehp2. you are
running&per. 
.br
:li.
Look in the root directory of your boot drive for a
file named :font facename='Courier' size=18x12.XFLDTRAP&per.LOG:font facename=default size=0x0.&per. This file logs XWorkplace's
exceptions which might have occured on your system&per.
If it exists, please include it in your message&per.

.br
:li.
If you are experiencing problems during WPS startup,
enable the :font facename='Courier' size=18x12.XWPSTART&per.LOG:font facename=default size=0x0. file on the "Startup" page
in the Desktop's settings notebook (assuming that you
can still get there)&per. This will create a file of
the same name in the root directory of the boot drive
during WPS startup&per. Please include this file also&per.

.br
:li.
If you are running into problems with the eXtended Shutdown
/ Restart Desktop features, please switch on the automatic
log function on the "Shutdown" page of the Desktop's
settings notebook&per. This will create a file named
:font facename='Courier' size=18x12.XSHUTDWN&per.LOG:font facename=default size=0x0. in the same location during shutdown&per.
Please include this file also&per. 
:eul.
:p.

.* Source file: "notices_40source.html"
:h2 res=10026 x=right width=70%.XWorkplace Source Code
:p.
XWorkplace is an open source project&per. As opposed
to previous XFolder versions, the source code now entirely
resides on the :link reftype=hd res=10150.OS/2 Netlabs:elink. server&per. 
:p.
We use the Concurrent Versioning System (CVS) to cooperatively
work on the source code&per. Basically this means that
there is a common source tree on an Internet server
(in this case, the one of Netlabs) which allows multiple
people to work on the sources at the same time&per.
CVS is then responsible for keeping all the changes
in sync&per. At :link reftype=hd res=10100.http&colon.//www&per.xworkplace&per.org:elink.,
you will find instructions where to find the sources,
including detailed instructions about how to use CVS&per.

