.* Source file: "intro_0motiv.html"
:h2 res=10030 x=right width=70%.Welcome to XWorkplace!
:p.

:artwork name='xfolder.bmp' runin align=left.
:p.
Welcome to XWorkplace! 
:p.
XWorkplace is intended to become the universal Workplace
Shell (WPS) enhancer&per. It is supposed to add lots
of useful features to many parts of your system, while
being totally configurable, so that all features you
don't like can be turned off&per. 
:p.
XWorkplace has evolved from the popular :hp2.XFolder:ehp2. utility&per.
However, since XFolder started to manipulate many more
things in the WPS than just folders, I chose to rename
the whole thing&per. Also, the package has been greatly
extended to justify the name change&per. 
:p.
While XFolder was OpenSource already, it was still mainly
developed by one person (Ulrich Mîller, that is, myself)&per.
By contrast, XWorkplace is a truly open project on the
Netlabs CVS server, so that more programmers can easily
join and contribute&per. See :link reftype=hd res=10026."XWorkplace source code":elink.
for details&per. 
:p.
At this point, XWorkplace already contains the features
of XFolder, WarpEnhancer, and XPager, and adds adds
even more completely new features which were not present
in these packages yet&per. 
:p.
In my view, the WPS ist still the one feature which
makes OS/2 stand out compared to other operating systems&per.
While other operating systems (especially Linux) have
by now reached a stability which is at least comparable,
if not greater than OS/2's, there is nothing that I
know of which can compare to the WPS in terms of productivity,
flexibility and superior overall concept&per. 
:p.
However, there are a number of things in the WPS which
are truly annoying and which IBM hasn't cared to fix
so far, and probably never will&per. 
:p.
So XWorkplace contains exactly those features I have
missed working daily with OS/2; I hope that you consider
XWorkplace just as useful as I do&per. 
.br

.* Source file: "intro_1overview.html"
:h2 res=10031 x=right width=70%.Overview
:p.
XWorkplace has several "subcomponents", if you want&per.
Most of the new features are hooked into the WPS by
replacing a number of WPS classes&per. 
:p.
:hp2.Note&colon.:ehp2. Most XWorkplace features are disabled per
default to prevent problems already after XWorkplace
has been installed, because these might cause problems
on some systems&per. In order to get these to work,
open the new :hp2."XWorkplace Setup" object:ehp2. and go to the
"Features" page, where you will find everything&per.
See :link reftype=hd res=10011.XWorkplace Settings Objects:elink. for details&per. 
:ol compact.:li.
The Workplace Shell folder class (WPFolder) is replaced
with a new class, :hp2.XFolder,:ehp2. to introduce a lot of new
folder functionality&per. 
:p.
This includes :link reftype=hd res=10042.freely configurable context menus,:elink. quick
display of :link reftype=hd res=10044.folder contents:elink. in context menus, display
of the :link reftype=hd res=10048.full folder path:elink. in a folder's window title,
the prettiest and most flexible :link reftype=hd res=10056.folder status bars:elink. on
the planet, extended :link reftype=hd res=10050.folder sort functions,:elink. :link reftype=hd res=10051.auto-scrolling
of Tree views:elink., :link reftype=hd res=10053.folder hotkeys:elink. for frequently used folder/file
operations, and more&per. 
.br
:li.
XWorkplace allows you to :link reftype=hd res=10014.replace the system icons:elink. for
the most common object classes&per. 
.br
:li.
XWorkplace enhances the WPS's :link reftype=hd res=10007.file operations:elink. by adding
:link reftype=hd res=10060.extended file associations:elink. and adding a trash can for
"delete" operations&per. 
.br
:li.
And then there's lots of extra functionality for :hp2.system
startup and shutdown&colon.:ehp2. preparing folders for :link reftype=hd res=10052.QuickOpen:elink.
at Desktop startup, freely configurable :link reftype=hd res=10066.Desktop start
logos,:elink. a :link reftype=hd res=10067."Restart Desktop":elink. feature which doesn't ruin
your WPS settings, :link reftype=hd res=10068.Extended Shutdown:elink. with a number of
very useful enhancements, new :link reftype=hd res=10069.Startup / Shutdown folders,:elink.
automated :link reftype=hd res=10065.WPS archiving:elink., and more&per. 
.br
:li.
XWorkplace also enhances your :link reftype=hd res=10009.mouse and keyboard functionality:elink.
by introducing a sliding focus, screen border objects,
and global object hotkeys&per. This includes :link reftype=hd res=10010.XPager,:elink.
a virtual desktop utility which has been integrated
into XWorkplace&per. 
.br
:li.
For configuration, XWorkplace creates additional settings
object in your "System setup" folder&per. See :link reftype=hd res=10011."XWorkplace
Settings Objects":elink. for an overview&per. 
.br
:li.
XWorkplace can also :link reftype=hd res=10013.enhance Multimedia:elink. on your system&per.

.br
:li.
Finally, we also have a WarpCenter replacement now --
the :link reftype=hd res=10015.XCenter:elink.&per. 
:eol.
:p.

.br

.* Source file: "intro_2opensource.html"
:h2 res=10032 x=right width=70%.Why OpenSource?
:p.
With V0&per.80, XFolder was placed under the GNU General
Public Licence (GPL), and XWorkplace will continue to
be shipped under that licence&per. 
:p.
The GPL is a general licence agreement which was developed
by the Free Software Foundation to protect the rights
of programmers who wish to publish the source code of
their software&per. The GPL is most frequently used
with software of the GNU project and has become more
widely known with the evolution of Linux, to most parts
of which the GPL applies&per. 
:p.
If you're interested in finding out more about OpenSource
licencing models and why I think that all OS/2 freeware
developers should release their source codes, preferrably
