.* Source file: "intro_2request.html"
:h2 res=10033 x=right width=70%.Request For Help
:p.
If you like XWorkplace and would like to contribute
to it, your support will be very welcome&per. XWorkplace
is slowly beginning to become too complex to be handled
by one person all alone&per. 
:ul compact.:li.
:hp2.Translations&per.:ehp2. XWorkplace is designed to be translateable
in a fairly easy way&per. All language-dependent parts
have been separated from the actual "intelligence" of
the program into separate files, which can be translated
independently&per. 
:p.
If you're interested in :hp2.translating XWorkplace to your
language,:ehp2. you can simply download the XWorkplace sources
from my homepage, which contain everything necessary
for this&per. You don't have to be a programmer to do
this, but it would be of great help if you have a basic
knowledge of HTML, since both XWorkplace's Online Reference
and the help file were originally written in HTML and
then simply converted to the IBM format, which I dislike
very much&per. 
:p.
In this case, please contact me, so I can add you to
my mailing list to allow you to get news about changes
in time&per. 
.br
:li.
If you're a programmer and have some experience in :hp2.PM
and/or WPS programming,:ehp2. please contact me also&per.
We have great plans for XWorkplace's future to overcome
the most obvious WPS limitations which exist today&per.
Since there's little hope that IBM will do anything
about this, I believe the OS/2 community needs to do
it themselves&per. The following major things are on
the to-do list&colon. 
.br

:ol compact.:li.
:hp2.WPS file handling&per.:ehp2. This needs some serious reworking&per.
I cannot believe that the WPS hangs every other time
one copies more than a dozen files&per. File handling
is the main task of an operating system's shell, and
the current implementation needs at least the following
enhancements&colon. thread-safety, speed, proper progress
bars when copying, a "Cancel" button that's not always
disabled, more meaningful error messages etc&per.pp&per.
This will require all of the WPS file-handling methods
to be reworked (:font facename='Courier' size=18x12.wpCopy:font facename=default size=0x0., :font facename='Courier' size=18x12.wpMove:font facename=default size=0x0. etc&per.)&per. 
.br
:li.
:hp2.Icon handling&per.:ehp2. Drag'n'drop in the WPS always causes
icons to be arranged in a fairly random way&per. This
should be improved&per. 
.br
:li.
:hp2.WPProgram&per.:ehp2. I have never understood why there's an
object for global DOS/Win-OS/2 settings if the program
objects don't respect the settings there&per. We need
support for global settings and also global and individual
environment variables in program objects so that :font facename='Courier' size=18x12.CONFIG&per.SYS:font facename=default size=0x0.
does not always have to be modified&per. 
.br
:li.
:hp2.WarpCenter&per.:ehp2. That thing is instable, slow, and does
not conform very well with the rest of the WPS&per.
This should be completely reprogrammed&per. Since XWorkplace
already has code for those "folder content" menus, this
shouldn't be too hard to to&per. 
.br
:li.
:hp2.Multi-user support&per.:ehp2. The WPS is already designed
to support multiple users thru the use of multiple OS2&per.INI
files and Desktop hierarchies, so I cannot quite understand
why IBM is not implementing this&per. XWorkplace could
do this; I am thinking of replacing the PROTSHELL and/or
RUNWORKPLACE statements in :font facename='Courier' size=18x12.CONFIG&per.SYS:font facename=default size=0x0. with some
XWorkplace executable, which will then start PMSHELL&per.EXE
with a bunch of preset environment variables, most importantly
OS2&per.INI settings and a UNIX-like HOME environment
variable to support multiple configurations for applications
in a "home" directory for each user&per. XWorkplace
should then offer a context menu item to "logoff" or
something&per. 
.br
:li.
OS/2 also needs to be able to :hp2.restart Presentation Manager:ehp2.
somehow without having to reboot, for example to change
display resolutions&per. The current solution is a joke&per.
If you have any ideas about this, especially how to
terminate and restart PM without blocking the system,
please contact me&per. 
:eol.
:p.
So if you're interested in adding any of these features
to XWorkplace (or if you have other suggestions), you'd
be very welcome to join the project! Any help is appreciated&per.

:eul.
:p.

.br

