.* Source file: "fldr_60defaultdoc.html"
:h2 res=10054 x=right width=70%.Folder Default Documents
:p.
Starting with V0&per.9&per.4, XWorkplace allows you
to define a "default document" for a folder&per. 
:p.
Default documents are initially disabled&per. Go to
the "View" page of the :link reftype=hd res=10083."Workplace Shell" object:elink. to enable
them&per. 
:p.
If default documents are enabled, this will have two
consequences&colon. 
:ol compact.:li.
All :hp2.data files:ehp2. will get a new context menu item called
"Default document"&per. This item allows you to make
a data file the default document of its folder&per.

.br
:li.
If such a default document has been set for a folder,
that :hp2.folder:ehp2. will have a new menu item in its "Open"
context submenu which allows you to open that default
document directly&per. Note the difference&colon. the
:hp1.folder:ehp1. context menu item opens the :hp1.data file&per.:ehp1. This
is useful for folders which have a "main" file which
is frequently opened in order to avoid having to open
the entire folder just to access that one document all
the time&per. 
:eol.
:p.
In addition, you can even tell XWorkplace to automatically
make that default document the :hp2.folder's default view&per.:ehp2.
If this is also enabled on the "View" page of the :link reftype=hd res=10083."Workplace
Shell" object,:elink. the default :hp1.document:ehp1. will be opened if
you double-click on the :hp1.folder:ehp1. icon&per. 
:p.
If you don't want this to be the standard behavior for
all folders which have default documents, you can always
set the default view of an individual folder to the
"default document" view on the "Menu" page of the folder's
settings notebook&per. 
:p.
Here's an :hp2.example&colon.:ehp2. Say you have a folder with
300 HTML files&per. Opening the folder just to access
the :font facename='Courier' size=18x12.index&per.html:font facename=default size=0x0. file is really tiresome because this
takes some time, and you really only want to access
the :font facename='Courier' size=18x12.index&per.html:font facename=default size=0x0. file&per. 
:p.
So open the folder once, open the context menu of :font facename='Courier' size=18x12.index&per.html:font facename=default size=0x0.,
select "Default document", and you can simply double-click
on the folder to have :font facename='Courier' size=18x12.index&per.html:font facename=default size=0x0. opened from now
on&per. 
.br

