.* Source file: "nsd_1intro.html"
:h2 res=10084 x=right width=70%.Introduction
:p.

:artwork name='netscdde.bmp' runin align=left.
:p.
Are you too annoyed too by the fact that double-clicking
on a URL or HTML file on your hard disk will always
start a new instance of NETSCAPE&per.EXE, although Netscape
is already running? This is a waste of time, memory,
and system resources&per. 
:p.
The :hp2.Netscape DDE Interface:ehp2. is the solution&per. You
can associate it with HTML and URL files, so that when
you double-click on them, either Netscape will be started
or, if it's already running, the HTML file or URL will
simply be passed to the running instance&per. 
:p.
NetscapeDDE should work with all of Netscape 2&per.02,
4&per.04, and 4&per.61 for OS/2&per. Since Mozilla presently
does not have DDE support (as of 2001-06-03), it won't
work with any of the current Mozilla-based browsers
though&per. 
.br

.* Source file: "nsd_2install.html"
:h2 res=10085 x=right width=70%.Installation
:p.
There is no real installation for NetscDDE because XWorkplace
comes preconfigured to let you use it&per. The :link reftype=hd res=10040.default
configuration:elink. adds a "Netscape DDE" item to all folder
context menus which displays the contents of that folder
in Netscape&per. 
:p.
However, there are a few extra things you can do with
NetscDDE&per. 
:ol compact.:li.
Create a program object for the :font facename='Courier' size=18x12.NETSCDDE&per.EXE:font facename=default size=0x0. file
