.* Source file: "vers_2about.html"
:h2 res=10101 x=right width=70%.About XWorkplace Version Numbering
:p.
With the release of XWorkplace V0&per.9&per.0, the :hp2.version
numbering format has been altered&per.:ehp2. Similar to the
Linux version numbering, we now have three sub-digits
in the version number, which is now in the format :font facename='Courier' size=18x12.major&per.minor&per.revision:font facename=default size=0x0.&per.

:p.
As with Linux, :hp2.odd minor numbers:ehp2. are used for "developer
releases" which are not guaranteed to be stable&per.
After several developer releases, if the code is considered
to be stable, the next version will get an :hp2.even minor
number&per.:ehp2. 
:p.
So version 1&per.0&per.0 means that the code is considered
ready for general use&per. 
.br

.* Source file: "vers_2history77_1_0_1.html"
:h2 res=10102 x=right width=70%.XWorkplace 1.0.1
:p.
Pure bugfix release off the 1&per.0 branch&per. "Bug
#" numbers refer to the official XWorkplace bugtracker
at :link reftype=hd res=10149.http&colon.//xtracker&per.netlabs&per.org:elink.&per. :hp2.
:p.
XWorkplace 1&per.0&per.1 (February 2, 2003):ehp2. 
:p.
Miscellaneous changes&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
Common&colon. Removed global "resize settings pages"
setting, which is always enabled now&per. (Bug #285,
286) 
.br
:li.
Common&colon. Removed the annoying "hwndDaemonObject
is NULLHANDLE" log message on every startup&per. (Bug
#64) 
.br
:li.
Turbo folders&colon. Removed the "extended associations"
setting, which is now combined with the "turbo folders"
setting&per. Using only one of them proved to make the
system unstable, and this turned out to be impossible
to fix without a lot of effort&per. 
.br
:li.
Folder split views&colon. Sped up emptying containers
on folder change&per. (Bug #270) 
.br
:li.
Pager&colon. Adjusted default window position to not
overlap eCenter&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. made introductory help a global setting&per.

.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Removed the xwhealth widget from the
distribution, since the author has a more up-to-date
version on his web page and no longer supplies me with
updates&per. The one from previous versions should still
work&per. 
:eul.
:p.
Bugfixes&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
Common&colon. Fixed XWPProgram class breaking the entire
WPS class setup during initialization&per. (Bug #266)

.br
:li.
Common&colon. Mouse pointer was sometimes set wrong
over my containers with checkboxes&per. Fixed&per. (Bug
#266) 
.br
:li.
Folder split views&colon. Fixed a dangling pointer in
folder background loading&per. 
.br
:li.
Folder split views&colon. Preventing the Desktop from
ever opening in split view&per. (Bug #325) 
.br
:li.
Folder split views&colon. Folders created with "Create
New" under disk object did not appear immediately&per.
Fixed&per. (Bug #284) 
.br
:li.
Batch-rename objects&colon. Raised internal buffer size
to avoid "string too long" messages for longer filenames&per.

.br
:li.
Lazy icon loading/shadow icons&colon. Fixed blank icons
of shadows to folders&per. (Bug #329) 
.br
:li.
Lazy icon loading/shadow icons&colon. Fixed ICO/PTR
files being reset to assoc icons&per. (Bug #293) 
.br
:li.
Folder refresh&colon. XWorkplace now correctly detects
when a &per.LONGNAME EA has changed&per. (Bug #238)

.br
:li.
Font folder&colon. Fixed wrong error message&per. (Bug
#36) 
.br
:li.
File operations&colon. "Title clash" dialog frequently
had no checkbox enabled, even though it worked correctly
otherwise&per. (Bug #229) 
.br
:li.
WPS class list&colon. fixed trap on open&per. (Bug #243)

.br
:li.
OS/2 kernel&colon. POPUPLOG drive was wrong&per. Fixed
by Paul Ratcliffe&per. (Bug #37) 
.br
:li.
OS/2 kernel&colon. CLASSPATH system path was wrong&per.
Fixed by Paul Ratcliffe&per. (Bug #272) 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. "Reduce desktop workarea" finally positions
maximized windows without overlapping&per. (Bug #246)

.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Object buttons that pointed to now invalid
objects would cause internal traps in PM because the
icon handle was wrong&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Tray widget now remembers background
color&per. (Bug #58) 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Changing top/bottom location of XCenter
wrongly set a screen border action&per. Fixed&per. (Bug
#252) 
:eul.
:p.

.* Source file: "vers_2history78_1_0_0.html"
:h2 res=10103 x=right width=70%.XWorkplace 1.0.0
:p.
Yes, 1&per.0&per.0 is out&per. 
:p.
As a general change, this release will most probably
no longer run on Warp 3 since I am overriding quite
a number of WPS methods now that are specific to OS/2
Warp 4&per. I was getting tired of hacking around menu
specifics for Warp 4 and am now using Warp 4's interfaces
for that&per. 
:p.
I have gotten no reports about Warp 3 recently so I
assume this will not break XWorkplace for a lot of people&per.
To those who are still running Warp 3, I am sorry, but
Warp 4 is six years old by now as well and it should
be possible to get it cheap somewhere&per. Otherwise,
stick with XWorkplace V0&per.9&per.20&per. :hp2.
:p.
XWorkplace 1&per.0&per.0 (November 24, 2002):ehp2. 
:p.
New features&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
Common&colon. Added "Report bug" button to XWorkplace
product info dialog&per. :hp2.Please use that button for
all bug reports from now on&per.:ehp2. Thank you&per. 
.br
:li.
Startup&colon. XWorkplace is now checking the WPS's
class replacements list on startup to make sure that
XFldObject is the first replacement of WPObject&per.
This should fix the problems with the "Speech" tab missing
when VoiceType is installed, hopefully&per. 
.br
:li.
Folder split views&per. Enable them in "XWorkplace Setup"
and select "Split view" from a folder's "open" menu&per.

.br
:li.
OS/2 Kernel, program files&colon. bldlevel parser can
now handle the weird format that is used by IBM TCP/IP&per.

.br
:li.
Disks&colon. Fixed a bunch of weirdos in the WPS disk
context menus&per. For one, the IBM peer class replacements
kept showing the "drive not ready" hard error TWICE
when requesting the context menu for a drive with no
media&per. Secondly, the WPS seemed to be using the
system uptime to determine whether "Lock" and "Eject"
should be shown for removeable disks&per. "Lock" and
"Eject" are now always shown&per. Both features are
only enabled when the "Replace drive not ready" feature
is enabled, for security&per. 
.br
:li.
XPager&colon. Martin Lafaix added "Sticky" menu option
to system menus&per. 
:eul.
:p.
Miscellaneous changes&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
Common&colon. Rewrote large parts of the dialog formatter
to allow for easier handling of nested subtables in
dialog descriptions&per. 
.br
:li.
Common&colon. Me smartass finally figured out that declaring
functions as "static" will never put them into the linker's
map files&per. As a result, they didn't end up the SYM
files either, which made XWorkplace's trap logs a lot
less informative&per. Fixed, I removed all "static"
declarations for now&per. :hp2.Note&colon.:ehp2. I discovered a
problem with XWorkplace's SYM files since XFLDR&per.DLL
has finally become too big to handle all the symbols&per.
As a result, the trap logs might contain some garbage
lines&per. I am still thinking about how to fix this&per.

.br
:li.
Folder menus&colon. Rewrote and adjusted large parts
of the internal menu hacks to get split views to work&per.
I hope this hasn't broken anything for the default (icon,
tree, details) folder views&per. 
.br
:li.
Folder menus&colon. Turned "Copy filename" into a submenu
to get rid of the unintuitive shift-click thing and
added a few more menu items if multiple files are selected&per.

.br
:li.
Folder hotkeys&colon. Martin Lafaix rewrote the respective
page in "Workplace Shell"&per. 
:eul.
:p.
Bugfixes&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
Common&colon. Executable header parser was completely
broken for files without extensions (e&per.g&per. OS2KRNL)&per.
Fixed; "Module" page now displays correctly&per. 
.br
:li.
Common&colon. XWorkplace kept the default OS/2 shutdown
from finishing, at least with IBM MCP2&per. Fixed&per.

.br
:li.
Common&colon. Changed a a number of places that requested
object mutexes too frequently and made them use private
mutexes instead&per. That fixed several situations where
the WPS deadlocked because of mutexes requested in reverse
order by two different threads&per. Among others, this
fixes the hangs during installation (instl001&per.cmd)
on SMP and when dragging attachments from PMMail to
the Desktop&per. Thanks to Knut St&per. Osmundsen for
helping with debugging this&per. 
.br
:li.
Folders&colon. "Create new" from template in config
folder never worked really well in Tree views&per. Fixed
a few things&per. 
.br
:li.
Folders&colon. Status bars produced vertical scroll
bars for all folders that had "always sort" off&per.
Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Folders&colon. Paul Ratcliffe fixed several duplicate
menu items and added a config option for "Restart Desktop"&per.

.br
:li.
Folders&colon. If always sort was off, scroll bars would
keep popping up randomly&per. Fixed, I hope&per. 
.br
:li.
Folder hotkeys&colon. Martin Lafaix rewrote the settings
page in "Workplace Shell"&per. 
.br
:li.
Folder hotkeys&colon. Disabled select by name, select
all, and deselect all for Tree views finally&per. 
.br
:li.
Folder sort&colon. Settings were quite broken for newly
created folders sometimes&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Select by name, Batch rename&colon. Always popped up
twice when invoked from a context menu&per. Fixed; added
folder title to dialog title while I was at it&per.

.br
:li.
Startup and Shutdown folders&colon. Folder titles were
never localized&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Folder painting&colon. "shadow icons" produced strange
display for shadowed folders in Tree view&per. Fixed&per.

.br
:li.
Extended associations&colon. "Export" facility did not
escape attribute values like &amp. properly&per. Fixed&per.

.br
:li.
Extended associations&colon. After setting the icon
of a data file object, changing its title would replace
the custom icon with that of the associated program&per.
Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
File operations&colon. If deletion of a data file failed,
e&per.g&per. because it was currently used, the WPS
object was removed anyway without an error message&per.
Fixed, added meaningful error messages also&per. 
.br
:li.
File dialog&colon. Mostly reimplemented to share the
new split view code&per. 
.br
:li.
Programs&colon. Fixed problems with %* replacements&per.
For one, %**N and the like are now case-insensitive
(as with the WPS, that is, %**n is recognized also)&per.
Secondly, XWorkplace put quotes around %* placeholders
(including %**N and the like) when the result had spaces,
but the WPS doesn't&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Programs&colon. Replacement icon code for program objects
never looked for &per.ICON EAs with executable, but
always searched the executable resources only&per. Among
others, PMView suffered from this, displaying a dull
standard PM icon&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Programs&colon. Knut St&per. Osmundsen fixed some problems
with passing environments on program startup&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Mostly rewrote pulse widget graph painting
to fix the vertical lines on the left if a high load
was displayed&per. Optimized the code at the same time
to save a few hundered Gpi* calls&per. 
.br
:li.
WPS class list&colon. crashed when selecting an orphaned
WPS class&per. Bug was introduced with 0&per.9&per.20,
fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
OS/2 Kernel&colon. Syslevels page didn't find syslevel
files if they were not on the boot drive&per. Fixed,
we now search the PATH for where the networking components
might be&per. 
.br
:li.
OS/2 Kernel, program files&colon. bldlevel display missed
single-character substrings in extended bldlevel format
(e&per.g&per. DANIS506&per.ADD)&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Hook&colon. Martin Lafaix fixed a few weirdos with auto-hide
mouse&per. 
.br
:li.
Netscape DDE&colon. finally passes URLs with "?" characters
correctly&per. 
:eul.
:p.

.* Source file: "vers_2history79_0_9_20.html"
:h2 res=10104 x=right width=70%.XWorkplace 0.9.20
:p.
:hp2.XWorkplace 0&per.9&per.20 (August 11, 2002):ehp2. 
:p.
New features&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
Documented XWPString setup strings&per. Added XWPString
NOSTRINGPAGE setup string&per. Added XFldDesktop SHOWHELPPANEL
setup string&per. 
.br
:li.
Giant WPS help rework&per. XWorkplace can now replace
most default WPS help panels&per. This can be disabled
on the "Features" page in XWPSetup&per. 
.br
:li.
Extended associations&colon. Added icon sharing&per.
If the icon of a program object is changed, all data
files using that object's icon are finally properly
refreshed&per. The feature is enabled automatically
with extended associations and works only with them,
unfortunately&per. To quote Achim HasenmÅller&colon.
"I've been waiting for that functionality since OS/2
2&per.0 beta&per."&per. 
.br
:li.
Extended associations&colon. Added a new setting to
"File types" page that allows you to disable passing
the object handle of a data file to the environment
of the associated program&per. 
.br
:li.
File operations&colon. Added replacement "Paste" dialog
(from "Edit" menu) because I finally got sick of the
default WPS one&per. The replacement can be enabled
on the "Features" page as well&per. 
.br
:li.
Folders&colon. Added lazy icon loading for folder populate,
which makes folders show icons much more quickly initially
and loads the real object icons asynchronously on a
separate thread&per. This can be enabled in "Workplace
Shell", "Folder Views" page and should work even if
turbo folders or extended associations are disabled&per.

.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Window list widget has a "Filter" menu
item in the button context menu now for quicker filtering&per.

.br
:li.
XPager&colon. Selecting "Properties" from the pager
context menu opens the "XPager" page in the "Screen"
object directly now&per. 
.br
:li.
XPager&colon. Shift + MB2 click on an empty area in
the pager hides the pager immediately now&per. 
:eul.
:p.
Miscellaneous changes&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
Common&colon. XWorkplace no longer holds all messages
from the TMF file in memory, reducing memory usage&per.

.br
:li.
Common&colon. Greatly optimized nlsUpper, my helper
func for upper-casing a string that gets called from
nearly everywhere&per. 
.br
:li.
Common&colon. Optimized a lot of internal management
routines to use less memory and no longer use the XWorkplace
heap by moving linked list pointers into object instance
memory&per. Awake objects management is no longer done
by the Worker thread either&per. 
.br
:li.
Common&colon. Optimized my object destruction mechanism
to no longer use SOM name lookup method resolution,
since I found a way to handle undocumented WPS methods
better&per. 
.br
:li.
Common&colon. Rewrote the XWorkplace "Product info"
dialog as a testcase for linking from my rich text control&per.

.br
:li.
File operations&colon. Reworked replacement "File exists"
dialog&per. 
.br
:li.
Replacement refresh&colon. Tweaked thread priorities
a bit to catch more file-system notifications&per. 
.br
:li.
Turbo folders&colon. Tweaked thread priorities a bit
to work better on uni-processor systems&per. 
.br
:li.
Trash can&colon. Is now smart enough to use DosForceDelete
in order not to move all files to DELDIR (if enabled)
on emptying the trash can&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Reworked all widget context menus to
make them more accessible&per. 
.br
:li.
XShutdown&colon. On "Restart Desktop", if "close all
sessions" is off, pager recovers only WPS windows to
current screen, while others keep running on their own
screens&per. 
:eul.
:p.
Bugfixes&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
Install&colon. Fixed several problems with installation
objects&per. 
.br
:li.
Common&colon. Replaced all strchr and strrchr calls
in XWorkplace with a DBCS-enabled version, of which
I do not know whether it actually works&per. I'd be
grateful if Asian testers could check whether the bugs
that have been reported are fixed by this since, again,
I have no way of testing DBCS here&per. 
.br
:li.
Common&colon. Replaced most wpQueryDefaultHelp overrides
with wpclsQueryDefaultHelp overrides for changing a
class's default help&per. The previous implementation
broke instance help assigned via HELPLIBRARY and HELPPANEL&per.

.br
:li.
Common&colon. Fixed rare synchronization problems when
objects were renamed and views sometimes not updated
properly&per. 
.br
:li.
Common&colon. Fixed a nasty object ID problem that would
cause CHECKINI to report lots of bad object IDs when
objects were created from the "Create new" folder menu&per.

.br
:li.
Common&colon. Fixed a problem during object deletion
that could cause the object to re-add information to
the INI files&per. This was probably the cause for CHECKINI
to report abstract objects that had been deleted by
XWorkplace&per. 
.br
:li.
Common&colon. All XWorkplace message boxes were lacking
the top-right "Close" button&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
"Icon" page replacement&colon. Fixed excessive rename
when page was first opened&per. 
.br
:li.
Program objects&colon. Command line icons were broken
(in "Command Prompts" folder), and batch files and Win-OS/2
full screen objects didn't work at all&per. Fixed&per.

.br
:li.
File operations&colon. Replacement "File exists" dialog
never respected the auto-rename or auto-replace settings
on the "Title" page in "Workplace Shell"&per. Fixed&per.

.br
:li.
Folders&colon. Hotkey for "Select by name" (per default,
Ctrl+S) broke with V0&per.9&per.19&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Folders&colon. "Batch rename" dialog had problems enabling
the start rename button&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Folders&colon. Folder hotkey descriptions were either
wrong or missing in the items in the menu bar pulldowns&per.
Fixed, hopefully&per. 
.br
:li.
Extended associations&colon. Got rid of the internal
types cache that ate up lots of memory and had synchronization
problems anyway, leading to wrong associations sometimes&per.
Extended assocs are thus slightly slower now when folders
are populated, but it's barely noticeable&per. 
.br
:li.
Extended associations&colon. Fixed a bug in my object
handles cache where sometimes the wrong object got thrown
out of the cache&per. 
.br
:li.
Turbo folders&colon. Plugged a few more holes where
the WPS succeeded in destroying object icons that were
assigned by XWorkplace, leading to blank icons&per.

.br
:li.
Replacement refresh&colon. Fixed a system deadlock in
the rare situation that an object was made awake from
the refresh thread that had an association icon that
was not previously used and thus had to be loaded first&per.

.br
:li.
Trash can&colon. Had serialization problems when several
views were populated at the same time&per. Fixed&per.

.br
:li.
Trash can&colon. Failed on deleting FTP folders&per.
Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Trash can / replacement delete&colon. Plugged another
hole where the WPS kept producing file-system handles
for objects just before deleting them&per. The handles
stayed in OS2SYS&per.INI forever, of course&per. This
was especially expensive when a folder with many subfolders
was deleted&per. 
.br
:li.
Fonts folder&colon. Reported "already installed" when
installing fonts if a font was previously deinstalled
without rebooting the system&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Fonts folder&colon. Status bar forgot how to count fonts
right when installing/deinstalling fonts&per. Fixed&per.

.br
:li.
Fonts folder&colon. Had serialization problems when
several views were populated at the same time&per. Fixed&per.

.br
:li.
Setup string objects&colon. If the default object stored
in the setup string object could not be resolved from
handle, double-clicking on the setup string object crashed
XWorkplace&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Sound object&colon. Sound scheme testing was case-sensitive,
while sound schemes in OS2SYS&per.INI are case-insensitive&per.
Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Screen object&colon. Special functions on screen border
objects page had funny titles, fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Diskfree (WarpCenter style) would never
save its width, fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
XShutdown&colon. Partitions listed on the "Partitions"
button in the user reboot actions dialog were truncated
to 8 characters, but LVM allows 20&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Hook&colon. Fixed raise window on MB1 clicks in certain
situations&per. Also fixed a couple items with Mozilla
menus&per. (Martin Lafaix) 
.br
:li.
XPager&colon. Fixed a couple of traps when the hook
was disabled manually&per. (Paul Ratcliffe) 
.br
:li.
XPager&colon. Removed silly "Pager is disabled" message
from "Add sticky window" dialog&per. 
.br
:li.
XPager&colon. Stay on top would never work, fixed&per.

.br
:li.
XPager&colon. If "Show secondary windows" was on, you
couldn't click on them in the pager&per. Not sure when
this broke or if this was even broken in 0&per.9&per.19,
but it works now&per. 
.br
:li.
XPager&colon. While Embellish was running, pager would
stop switching&per. Fixed&per. 
:eul.
:p.

.* Source file: "vers_2history80_0_9_19.html"
:h2 res=10105 x=right width=70%.XWorkplace 0.9.19
:p.
:hp2.XWorkplace 0&per.9&per.19 (July 2, 2002):ehp2. 
:p.
New features&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
Icon page&colon. Implemented keyboard support for editing
the object ID&per. 
.br
:li.
Folders&colon. "Select by name" dialog supports regular
expressions now&per. 
.br
:li.
Folders&colon. Added "Rename objects" folder context
menu item for batch renaming&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Added "IP monitor" widget&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. X-Button widget now opens its menu when
XCenter object hotkey is pressed&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. X-Button widget supports user bitmaps
now (open properties to set them)&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Per default, an XCenter makes itself
a screen border object automatically now&per. This can
be disabled in the settings notebook&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Widget context menus have "Close" menu
item now&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. WIDGETS setup strings supports trays
now&per. It is finally possible to set up a complete
XCenter via setup strings&per. Note that the format
has slightly changed; see the help for the object "Details"
button on the "Icon" page for details&per. Changed the
default XCenter setup while I was at it&per. 
.br
:li.
OS/2 Kernel&colon. Added a couple more SYSLEVEL files&per.

.br
:li.
Hook&colon. Added "Center over button-less dialogs"
to auto-move pointer feature (Martin Lafaix)&per. 
.br
:li.
XPager&colon. Reworked pager window display to allow
for shaded colors in background and showing the program
icons as well&per. 
.br
:li.
XPager&colon. Sticky window criteria are now much better;
"Undo" works now too (Martin Lafaix)&per. Also included
regular expressions support&per. 
.br
:li.
XPager&colon. Pager window can now paint sticky and
secondary windows too (Martin Lafaix)&per. 
.br
:li.
XPager&colon. "Desktop follows focus" can now be disabled,
for so many people didn't like this behavior&per. 
.br
:li.
NetscapeDDE&colon. uses default browser settings from
WPUrl object now, if not overridden from the command
line (Yuri Dario)&per. 
:eul.
:p.
Miscellaneous changes&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
Common&colon. Added better error messages for some error
codes&per. 
.br
:li.
Common&colon. Found a way to give dialog windows a close
button too&per. 
.br
:li.
Startup&colon. Much more detailed startup log which
might help debugging WPS startup problems&per. Changed
log file name to WPSTART&per.LOG&per. 
.br
:li.
Config folders&colon. The restriction that shadows to
program objects in the config folders were not treated
like program objects (for the special program object
features) has been lifted&per. It is no longer necessary
to copy program objects for that reason&per. 
.br
:li.
Folder content menus&colon. folder templates are no
longer sorted with the other folders&per. 
.br
:li.
File page replacement&colon. rewritten, it's now sizeable
too&per. 
.br
:li.
File operations&colon. Removed global "Replace true
delete" setting&per. Added a checkbox to trash can instead&per.

.br
:li.
File operations&colon. Reversed confirmations for "move
to trash" and "empty trash"&per. The real delete operation
is to move something to the trash can; it really doesn't
make sense to have every object confirmed when the trash
can is emptied later&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Single click on empty space in tray widget
will change trays now&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Made Diskfree (WarpCenter style) widget
sizeable to avoid the permanent resizing&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Rewrote large parts of the window list
widget, which no longer scans the window list itself,
but uses XWPDAEMN&per.EXE instead&per. For one, this
allows sharing the window list code between XPager and
the window list widget; most importantly though, the
window list no longer blocks the PM SIQ if a window
doesn't care to respond to WM_QUERYICON&per. Added half-toned
display for minimized and hidden windows as well&per.

.br
:li.
XShutdown&colon. We no longer recover Windows to the
current desktop and run the shutdown folder for "restart
Desktop", but only for actual system shutdown&per. 
.br
:li.
XPager&colon. The remaining parts of PageMage were rewritten&per.
There is now no legacy PageMage code left in XPager&per.
Optimized window list scanning to use an additional
background thread and to allow sharing the window list
with the XCenter window list widget&per. 
:eul.
:p.
Bugfixes&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
Common&colon. Some internal initialization code didn't
get called for folders, which was the reason why renaming
them neither refreshed their container record nor awake
shadows properly&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Common&colon. Fixed global variables which caused many
dialogs to fail after NLS change&per. Also localized
a few more hard-coded strings&per. 
.br
:li.
Common&colon. If NLS DLL cannot be found, XWorkplace
will automatically fall back to English NLS now&per.
Of course this doesn't work if English is broken, but
then XWorkplace is hosed anyway&per. 
.br
:li.
Common&colon. Lots of rework on dialog manager to fix
display oddities on resolutions lower than 1024x768&per.
Hopefully this didn't break anything&per. 
.br
:li.
Common&colon. Fixed tooltips that would frequently not
appear (Yuri Dario)&per. 
.br
:li.
Common&colon. Added help to some XWorkplace message
boxes&per. 
.br
:li.
Icon page replacement&colon. didn't allow empty object
titles, which is allowed in the WPS&per. Fixed&per.

.br
:li.
Programs&colon. Now using XWPDAEMN&per.EXE for starting
programs, which should help with applications hanging
the system&per. 
.br
:li.
Programs&colon. Selecting "Cancel" in parameters prompt
provoked a cryptic error message&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Programs&colon. Added a missing mutex semaphore which
might have caused hangs during WPS startup or later
when program data was changed&per. 
.br
:li.
Folder status bars&colon. Finally fixed status bars
for those Object Desktop classes that shouldn't have
any&per. 
.br
:li.
Folder status bars&colon. Fixed garbage display if more
than 4 GB of files were selected in a folder&per. 
.br
:li.
Folders&colon. "Select by name" never worked right from
"Edit" pulldown menu if any files were selected in the
folder view&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Folders&colon. Opening settings notebook could take
ages if turbo folders were off&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Folders&colon. Details views weren't refresh properly
during refresh&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Folders&colon. Turbo folders had a few situations where
real name changes weren't picked up properly, leading
to duplicate or misnamed objects&per. Among other things,
this could affect objects when the "Title clash" dialog
popped up&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Folder auto-refresh&colon. Fixed a couple cases where
refresh notifications were confused&per. 
.br
:li.
Folder content menus&colon. Text wasn't centered vertically
with icons, fixed (Martin Lafaix)&per. 
.br
:li.
Turbo folders&colon. Fixed wrong icons for FTP-PM and
other WPProgram subclasses&per. Also fixed wrong association
icons for WPUrl objects&per. 
.br
:li.
File operations&colon. True delete replacement never
worked if trash can was disabled&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
File operations&colon. Title clash dialog no longer
appears when creating shadows&per. 
.br
:li.
File operations&colon. Trash can crashed when deleting
several objects with the same title&per. Fixed&per.

.br
:li.
File dialog replacement&colon. Double-clicking on object
in right container didn't work&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Fonts folder&colon. Installing fonts via drag and drop
crashed the WPS internally&per. I'm not sure if the
bug was in 0&per.9&per.18 or if I introduced it later,
but it's working now anyway&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Largely rewrote widget creation and drag-n-drop
code to handle dragging widgets between XCenters, including
trays&per. Apparently this also fixed malpositioned
widgets in some situations&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Object button and X-button widgets crashed
PM bad when objects from other processes were dragged
over them&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Object buttons would frequently not repaint
correctly when hatching was supposed to disappear&per.
Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Double-clicking on clock widget didn't
quite open eCSClock correctly&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Finally saves its height between restarts
(Martin Lafaix)&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Object button content menus behaved strange
when XCenter border spacing was set to zero and the
object button was at the very left of the XCenter&per.
Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Some rework on DiskFree (WarpCenter style)
widget (Yuri Dario)&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Battery widget displayed wrong power
source when battery was fully charged on some systems&per.
Fixed, hopefully&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Fixed occasional zombie entries in system
window list&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Crash while processing a timer would
never release a private timer mutex, leading to system
hangs&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
XWPSetup&colon. "Create object" buttons produced empty
titles for some classes&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
XShutdown&colon. Fixed INI saving errors with empty
applications in profiles (Paul Ratcliffe)&per. 
.br
:li.
Hook&colon. Fixed major screwups if screen border objects
were opened during startup or shutdown&per. 
.br
:li.
Hook&colon. Pre-populate caused XPager to no longer
detect the WPS desktop&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Hook&colon. Fixed a race which caused XPager to ignore
the WPS desktop in certain conditions as well&per. 
.br
:li.
Hook&colon. Sliding focus never worked right with Mozilla
subwindows such as menus&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Hook&colon. "Function keys" page crashed if there were
no function keys&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
xfix&colon. Fixed crashes with some broken handles situations
(Paul Ratcliffe)&per. 
:eul.
:p.

.* Source file: "vers_2history81_0_9_18.html"
:h2 res=10106 x=right width=70%.XWorkplace 0.9.18
:p.
:hp2.XWorkplace 0&per.9&per.18 (March 26, 2002):ehp2. 
:p.
New features&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
Mouse&colon. Paul Ratcliffe added the "Screen wrap"
feature a la NPSWPS to the special actions for screen
borders&per. 
.br
:li.
Startup&colon. "Pre-populate desktop" feature&per. See
the "Features" page in XWPSetup&per. 
.br
:li.
XPager&colon. Holding down the "Shift" key while dragging
mini-windows in the pager window now drags across virtual
screens, keeping the window's position&per. Thanks,
Martin Lafaix&per. 
:eul.
:p.
Miscellaneous changes&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
Object button widgets are no longer shown in the "Add
widget" menu since they were always disabled anyway&per.

.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Now painting bottom 3D color in black
for better contrast&per. 
.br
:li.
Saved a precious PM timer in the Worker thread that
was used for close to nothing&per. 
.br
:li.
PageMage was renamed to XPager&per. This requires also
that you reconfigure the pager settings, unfortunately&per.

:eul.
:p.
Bugfixes&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
Common&colon. Fixed another problem with AM/PM (12-hour)
time display, which always ended up with "00&colon."
when "12&colon." should have been displayed&per. 
.br
:li.
File pages replacement&colon. Now refreshing page when
page is turned back to&per. 
.br
:li.
Program objects&colon. Fixed a bunch of problems with
programs not remembering setting changes and the bug
that program objects could no longer be properly created
at all&per. That was a hard one&per. Added exception
handling to a number of replacement methods too since
apparently the code crashed sometimes&per. Parts of
this code were and are active even if extended associations
were disabled&per. 
.br
:li.
Programs&colon. Fixed memory problems with my WinStartApp
wrapper which sometimes ate parts of the environment
of the process to be started&per. (The code was and
is active only if extended associations are enabled&per.)

.br
:li.
Programs&colon. Fixed hangs with VIO programs when not
started from thread 1&per. 
.br
:li.
Folder sorting / status bars&colon. Hopefully fixed
the mysterious scroll bars that would pop up in folder
icon views (in "as placed" mode) if "always sort" was
off for a folder&per. 
.br
:li.
Folder sorting&colon. "Sort by class" and "type" would
never sort if two objects had the same class or type&per.
Fixed, now falling back to sort by name for those cases&per.

.br
:li.
Turbo folders&colon. Miscellanous fixes for thread synchronization
problems which could lead to duplicate objects for the
same file&per. 
.br
:li.
Icon replacements&colon. Fixed missing icons with PMMail
attachments display&per. 
.br
:li.
Icon replacements&colon. Implemented wpQueryIconData
everywhere so that "Edit icon" and drag'n'drop show
the replacement icons too&per. 
.br
:li.
Icon replacements&colon. Custom icons in the &per.ICON
EA were ignored always and overridden by association
icon&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Icon replacements&colon. Fixed several places where
the WPS succeeded in killing my shared icons, resulting
in blank icons for a whole bunch of objects&per. 
.br
:li.
File dialog&colon. Large number of fixes for duplicate
objects in tree view plus frequent bad scrolling&per.

.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Knut St&per. Osmundsen fixed a bunch
of display problems introduced with the recent SMP update&per.
He reported this now works fine on SMP&per. Display
looks much better now&per. 
.br
:li.
XPager&colon. Martin Lafaix fixed a large number of
glitches with XPager's display plus some problems with
minimized/maximized windows&per. 
:eul.
:p.

.* Source file: "vers_2history82_0_9_17.html"
:h2 res=10107 x=right width=70%.XWorkplace 0.9.17
:p.
:hp2.XWorkplace 0&per.9&per.17 (February 5, 2002):ehp2. 
:p.
Miscellaneous changes&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
Added setting to XWPSetup "Features" page for whether
XWorkplace should check the desktop's integrity on startup,
since so many people had problems with it&per. Added
a corresponding flag to the "Panic" dialog also&per.

:eul.
:p.
Bugfixes&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
XWorkplace's "Check desktop" feature would report a
broken desktop even if only a single handle in the file-system
handles table was broken&per. Instead, XWorkplace now
gives you a different warning for that, allowing you
to display the "Panic" dialog instead and run xfix from
there&per. 
.br
:li.
After the dialog that popped up to tell XWorkplace about
the Desktop's location, the Desktop would be opened,
but the XFldDesktop class replacement would not be enabled
at all&per. Fixed; all XWorkplace features work in that
case too&per. 
.br
:li.
Programs&colon. Object data was never saved if the program
object had no program data, causing the "---" separators
in the config folder to never save their titles&per.
Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Daemon crashed if "Hide on click" was
enabled and hook wasn't active&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
XShutdown&colon. Paul Ratcliffe fixed XShutdown to no
longer hang with an empty message box on his system&per.

.br
:li.
xfix&colon. If the handles table was broken, xfix didn't
start but only displayed a cryptic error message&per.
Fixed, hopefully&per. 
:eul.
:p.

.* Source file: "vers_2history83_0_9_16.html"
:h2 res=10108 x=right width=70%.XWorkplace 0.9.16
:p.
:hp2.XWorkplace 0&per.9&per.16 (February 4, 2002):ehp2. 
:p.
New features&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
Common&colon. Instead of adding the "Object" page, XWorkplace
now completely replaces the "Icon" page in every settings
notebook&per. 
.br
:li.
Common&colon. Added "Replace file dialog" feature&per.
This only replaces file dialogs within the WPS, not
globally on the system&per. If enabled, XWorkplace code
will use a replacement file dialog with full WPS support
instead of the dull default OS/2 file dialog&per. Try
the "Browse" button on the new "Icon" page&per. 
.br
:li.
Folders&colon. Added new :link reftype=hd res=10049."turbo folders":elink. feature&per.

.br
:li.
Folders&colon. Finally documented that setup string
objects can be put into the XWorkplace Configuration
Folder as well to have the setup string invoked on the
folder whose context menu was selected&per. This feature
has been active for a while, but I forgot to document
it&per. 
.br
:li.
Folder content menus&colon. The folder's "Include" criteria
are finally fully respected so that objects which do
not match those criteria do not appear in the folder
content menus either&per. 
.br
:li.
File types&colon. Added icon display to "File types"
page in "Workplace Shell"&per. Also added "Properties"
and "Open folder" items to association context menu&per.

.br
:li.
Programs&colon. If extended associations are enabled,
all program files will now be started by XWorkplace,
circumventing any WPS code around WinStartApp&per. As
a side effect, this will give you more detailed error
messages if the program could not be started&per. 
.br
:li.
Trash can&colon. Added EMPTYTRASH=IMMEDIATE setup string&per.

.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. "Add widget" menu is now sorted alphabetically&per.
This was confusing&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Pulse widget now supports more than one
CPU on SMP systems, thanks to Bart van Leeuwen&per.
As a result the display is painting lines instead of
filled areas now&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Added "Properties" dialog to "Pulse"
widget to allow color configuration, finally&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Pulse widget now opens "OS/2 Kernel"
object on double-click&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. When XCenter is newly created, it comes
up with a standard widget setup now&per. The empty bar
confused many people initially&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Added setting for whether object button
widgets should show in-use emphasis (hatching)&per.

.br
:li.
XShutdown&colon. Screen is now dimmed as with Win95
while confirmation dialog is displayed&per. 
.br
:li.
XShutdown&colon. Pressing Alt+F4 while the Desktop has
the focus can now start shutdown&per. 
.br
:li.
Netscape DDE&colon. Added more command line options
for specifying the DDE server name and the startup directory,
which can make NetscDDE work with Mozilla too&per. Also
removed the dull dialog explaining the command line
options and added a proper help panel (shows up if you
double-click on NETSCDDE&per.EXE only)&per. 
.br
:li.
xfix&colon. Added object IDs display and deletion&per.

:eul.
:p.
Miscellaneous changes&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
Common&colon. Moved more pages from the INF to the HLP
file, such as :link reftype=hd res=10146.setup strings:elink.&per. In addition, WPProgram
setup strings are now documented also&per. 
.br
:li.
Common&colon. Reworked many dialogs and settings pages
to use my dialog formatter now&per. This makes changes
much easier and saves everyone from using the stupid
DLGEDIT any more (for those dialogs at least)&per. 
.br
:li.
Common&colon. Rework of the query-setup-string interfaces
to be less CPU-intensive&per. Also got rid of the danger
of synchronization problems between the two calls to
xwpQuerySetup that were always required&per. 
.br
:li.
Common&colon. Rewrote TMF loader to be much faster now&per.
XWorkplace now keeps its TMF file open all the time
and thus doesn't have to rebuild the strings buffer
for every message that is needed&per. 
.br
:li.
Common&colon. Rewrote Henk Kelder's WPS handles engine
to be much faster now&per. 
.br
:li.
Common&colon. Did lots of page tuning, both for frequently
used code and for the XWorkplace private heap&per. This
might result in speedups for certain time-critical places
such as folder populate and extended associations&per.

.br
:li.
Common&colon. Rewrote XWorkplace log file routines to
use DosWrite directly since the buffered fprintf() calls
sometimes didn't end up in the log at all (especially
on crashes)&per. 
.br
:li.
Common&colon. Per popular request, finally gave the
status dialogs the usual thick dialog borders&per. 
.br
:li.
Common&colon. Per popular request, reworked folder content
menu painting to always use at least the height of the
system mini icon size to avoid overlapping icons&per.

.br
:li.
Folders&colon. A private PMSHELL send-msg hook was registered
on WPS startup but never released even though it was
only used for the first folder that was ever opened&per.
Fixed; now removing the hook after the first folder
open&per. 
.br
:li.
Archiving&colon. Changed the settings format for the
WPS extended archiving&per. Please reconfigure&per.

.br
:li.
Font folder&colon. Per popular request, the font sample
display now displays fonts with the smallest sizes on
top&per. 
.br
:li.
Status bars&colon. are now respecting the default font
setting on the "Paranoia" page and using WarpSans by
default&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Stopped monitor widgets from shrinking
all the time&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Window list widget now always ignores
the Desktop and all open XCenters regardless of the
filters that were set&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Tray icon is now displayed vertically
to use up less space&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Added error logging around DosFreeModule
for widget DLLs; this might result in log entries for
some older widget DLLs which fail to unload themselves&per.
The most probable cause for this is that the DLL registered
an exit list entry which causes DosFreeModule to fail
always&per. 
:eul.
:p.
Bugfixes&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
Install&colon. "Mouse" shadow was never created in install
folder since IBM changed the object ID for the thing
for some reason&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Install&colon. Finally fixed the stupid error that CHECKINI
always reported on the <XWP_SEP42> object&per.
Thanks to John Small for the fix&per. 
.br
:li.
Common&colon. Run dialog would diplay the full path
of directories too, e&per.g&per. if "install" was entered&per.
Fixed; directories are now properly ignored&per. 
.br
:li.
Common&colon. Fixed several small memory leaks in various
places&per. 
.br
:li.
Common&colon. Fixed major/minor settings pages subtitles
(for notebook context menus) in various places&per.

.br
:li.
Common&colon. Removed all remaining must-complete sections
in the code which sometimes prevented PMSHELL from exiting
on kill or crashes&per. 
.br
:li.
Common&colon. Fixed a build problem which caused XWP
to fail on some Warp 3 systems since some of the Warp
4 SOM imports cannot be resolved there&per. 
.br
:li.
Common&colon. Paul Ratcliffe fixed a couple of cosmetic
things with the exception trap logs&per. 
.br
:li.
Common&colon. Fixed a bunch of wrong default template
settings for the XWP classes&per. 
.br
:li.
Common&colon. Fixed wrong owner windows for dialogs
created by the new dialog formatter, which, among other
things, affected the XWorkplace message boxes&per. Fixed
many misaligments and other cosmetic issues too&per.

.br
:li.
Common&colon. Paul Ratcliffe fixed bad AM/PM display
for 12&colon.00 noon in a library routine which, among
other things, affected the "Time" widget&per. 
.br
:li.
Common&colon. Added additional checks to an internal
populate routine which should now handle removeable
drives correctly&per. This should fix the problems with
folder content menus that removeable media changes weren't
picked up&per. 
.br
:li.
Startup&colon. Fixed endlessly looping startup folders&per.

.br
:li.
Icon replacemements&colon. While working on the program
icons replacement, I pretty much had to rewrite most
of the icon handling code in the WPS altogether&per.
As a side effect, I believe the problems with disappearing
icons and icons changing during refresh are now fixed
for good&per. 
.br
:li.
Object Details dialog&colon. Fixed crash if "No" was
selected in the confirmation dialog after changing the
object ID&per. 
.br
:li.
Programs&colon. Added more error checking to progOpenProgram&per.
Fixed more problems with programs not being started
from WPS thread 1, which can cause system hangs&per.
Also fixed problem that executable would not start if
it was not fully qualified in the program settings object,
but on the PATH only&per. 
.br
:li.
Disks&colon. Added more "drive ready" checks to context
menus and settings view to avoid some more "drive not
ready" popups&per. Note that context menus still show
"drive not ready" since that problem is in a WPS routine
I can't easily replace&per. 
.br
:li.
Folders&colon. MENUBAR setup string had a wrong default
value on Warp 4 and above&per. 
.br
:li.
Folders&colon. If the default folder view was set to
something other than "inherit" in "Workplace Shell",
changes in a folder's default view via the "Menu" page
(or the context menu item) were never picked up until
a Desktop restart&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Folders&colon. Replacement refresh code never picked
up RCNF_CHANGED notifications (which are quite rare
though)&per. Fixed, as well as some other missing notifications&per.

.br
:li.
Folders&colon. Added exception handling to an internal
populate helper which tended to crash on certain WPS
networking classes at times&per. 
.br
:li.
Extended associations&colon. If a data file had a type
set (either explicitly or automatically) but no associations
existed for that type, the "Open" submenu was empty&per.
Fixed; this now adds the associations for "Plain text"
to those objects too&per. 
.br
:li.
Status bars&colon. For remote disk objects (WPSharedDir),
the status bars kept querying drive A&colon. for the
free space, which was kind of annoying&per. The reason
was that WPShared&colon.&colon.wpQueryLogicalDrive returns
1 always for some reason only IBM can explain&per. Added
a special case check in a couple of places&per. 
.br
:li.
Status bars&colon. Fixed bad check for tree views which
sometimes failed to update themselves&per. 
.br
:li.
Status bars&colon. Fixed a bad exception handler cleanup&per.

.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Removed all the special window actication
handling for now&per. Besides, the XCenter frame is
no longer a PM WC_FRAME instance&per. Hopefully this
doesn't break anything else but fixes the stupid Mozilla
problems many people were having&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Fixed the 100% CPU load problem when
mouse was over XCenter while a settings dialog was showing&per.

.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Battery widget didn't repaint its background
properly when the power icon was changed&per. Fixed&per.

.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Fixed some bad clipping with object buttons&per.

.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Source emphasis for menus wasn't always
removed from client&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Fixed crashes with objects from other
processes being dragged over XCenter&per. 
.br
:li.
File operations&colon. Mostly rewrote the "Replace File
Exists" dialog to finally handle the "Create another"
and "Create from template" conditions correctly&per.
Besides, all the special case checks for FAT drives
were removed because the WPS handles all this correctly
already&per. 
.br
:li.
File operations&colon. Replacement delete never respected
the "Confirm folder deletion" setting from the "Confirmations"
page&per. Fixed; if this is enabled, you now get an
extra prompt before XWorkplace kills a folder&per. 
.br
:li.
Trash can&colon. Fixed wrong error message if "delete
to trash" was still enabled internally but the trash
can had disappeared for some reason&per. XWP is now
offering to recreate the trash can instead&per. 
.br
:li.
Trash can&colon. Fixed problems with UNC files&per.

.br
:li.
Trash can&colon. Dropping objects on the shredder would
move them into the trash can instead&per. Fixed; they
are now properly nuked&per. 
.br
:li.
Trash can / true delete&colon. Paul Ratcliffe fixed
a bunch of potential traps with NULL object titles&per.

.br
:li.
Trash can&colon. Disabled the stupid "File exists" dialog
that popped up if some other object with the same title
already existed in the same hidden trash directory&per.
Note that this will only work if you have "Replace file
exists" enabled, unfortunately&per. 
.br
:li.
Object hotkeys&colon. It was impossible to set a hotkey
into the "Hotkey" entry field that was already occupied&per.
Even worse, if the object had been lost, this kept the
entry field from working at all&per. Fixed; note that
this implies that you can now use the same hotkey for
several objects at once&per. 
.br
:li.
XPager&colon. XCenters are now sticky always and do
not have to be added manually to the "Stickies" list
any more&per. 
.br
:li.
XPager&colon. System window list would sometimes be
moved off to another screen and then be hard to see&per.
Made window list sticky always now&per. 
.br
:li.
XPager&colon. Repaint broke after XPager was disabled
and then re-opened&per. Fixed by Paul Ratcliffe&per.

.br
:li.
Hook&colon. Object hotkeys stopped working after screen
lockup, unless XPager was enabled&per. Fixed&per. Also
fixed the problem that it was possible to use hotkeys
before the Desktop was ready and during shutdown&per.

.br
:li.
Hook&colon. Now disabling sliding focus while "move
ptr to default button" is in progress&per. 
.br
:li.
XShutdown&colon. Paul Ratcliffe fixed bug trying to
close the first switch list item twice&per. 
.br
:li.
XShutdown&colon. I believe I have traced down and fixed
the problems with XShutdown and the "Desktop not found"
problem if XWorkplace is installed on multiple OS/2
partitions&per. The problem was quite deep in the WPS
internals and actually a WPS bug that was exposed by
the XWorkplace "save objects" function&per. For some
reason, the WPS kept deleting the <WP_DESKTOP>
object ID (and other object IDs) if they didn't match
the data in the current INI file, which of course they
don't if the object ID is from another WPS&per. Fixed
that; the object's instance data is now hacked to keep
the old object ID&per. 
.br
:li.
XShutdown&colon. Fixed hang on "Releasing filesystems"
on some systems, hopefully&per. I can't really assure
this since the bug never occured on my system, but XWorkplace
attempted to load one string resource after DosShutdown,
which really isn't a good idea&per.&per.&per. fixed
that&per. 
.br
:li.
Treesize&colon. Fixed a couple of long-standing cosmetic
problems&per. Added a decent help panel&per. 
:eul.
:p.

.* Source file: "vers_2history84_0_9_15.html"
:h2 res=10109 x=right width=70%.XWorkplace 0.9.15
:p.
:hp2.XWorkplace 0&per.9&per.15 (September 19, 2001):ehp2. 
:p.
This is an interim release for the IBM Warp Community
Workshop, September 17 to 21, 2001, Heidelberg, Germany&per.

:p.
New features&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
xfix&colon. Added "Select by name" function&per. 
:eul.
:p.
Miscellaneous changes&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
Resolved a couple of problems in the "WPS class list"
display&per.&per.&per. things that were supposed to
be working a long time ago but didn't, such as gray
display for classes that were replaced and automatic
expansion of the tree for those classes too&per. 
:eul.
:p.
Bugfixes&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
XPager&colon. Fixed sporadic hangs and blocks that occured
unreproducably, but reliably from time to time&per.
It appears that the problems have been fixed for good&per.

.br
:li.
Hook&colon. Animation for "Move pointer to default push
button" left circles on the screen in many cases; somewhat
fixed, although not completely&per. 
:eul.
:p.

.* Source file: "vers_2history85_0_9_14.html"
:h2 res=10110 x=right width=70%.XWorkplace 0.9.14
:p.
:hp2.XWorkplace 0&per.9&per.14 (August 26, 2001):ehp2. 
:p.
New features&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
General&colon. Added SHOWRUNDLG setup string&per. 
.br
:li.
General&colon. Since so many people didn't quite appreciate
my beautiful XWPSTART&per.LOG file, I added a setting
for that on the "Startup" page in the desktop's settings
notebook&per. 
.br
:li.
Mouse&colon. Martin Lafaix added a couple of settings
to the "Auto-hide mouse" feature and the general "Auto-move
pointer to default push button" feature&per. While I
was at it, I added mouse pointer animations then&per.

.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Added another diskfree widget ("condensed"
style)&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Added properties dlg to X-button widget
for configuring the menu items to display&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Added "Hide immediately on mouse click"
setting&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Martin Lafaix added dragging widgets
to open folders, which will create a widget definition
in a file, which can then be dropped to an XCenter again&per.
Experimental feature, no documentation yet&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Paul Ratcliffe added more options to
the "Run" dialog&per. 
.br
:li.
Treesize&colon. Added "100 largest files" function&per.

.br
:li.
Status bars&colon. Added "Keys" buttons to status bars
page 2 in "Workplace Shell" to list all the status bar
keys that are supported by the corresponding entry field&per.

:eul.
:p.
Miscellaneous changes&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
General&colon. Greatly sped up dialog engine by caching
font data, which affects the new message boxes, among
other things&per. 
.br
:li.
XWPSetup&colon. Reworked the "XWorkplace Classes" setup
dialog&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Optimized internal timers, which now
use less CPU time (depending on how many widgets are
running)&per. As a side effect, they are even much more
precise now&per. Thanks Martin Lafaix for the oriental
meditation hints&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Added more function imports to widget
DLLs to reduce their sizes&per. 
:eul.
:p.
Bugfixes&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
General&colon. New message boxes never had focus on
default button&per. Besides, the "snap back" for default
buttons on tabbing didn't always work&per. Fixed&per.

.br
:li.
General&colon. Some message boxes didn't react to mouse
clicks at all and could only be dismissed via keyboard&per.
Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
General&colon. Fixed a rounding problem in the font
engine which caused wrong font sized to be selected
in some situations&per. 
.br
:li.
General&colon. Fixed about a dozen memory leaks in various
places&per. 
.br
:li.
General&colon. Library routine which was used for starting
applications (among others, by XCenter "Run" dialog)
always hung the system for full-screen Win-OS/2 sessions&per.
Fixed by Paul Ratcliffe&per. 
.br
:li.
XFolder&colon. Folder hotkeys for sort and arrange sorted
the desktop even if the respective menu items were disabled
for the desktop&per. Fixed; these are suppressed now
to avoid accidentally sorting or arranging the desktop&per.

.br
:li.
XFolder&colon. Fixed a number of problems with "Create
another" in tree views, most notably that the new object
wouldn't appear unless the tree view had SHOWALLINTREEVIEW
set&per. 
.br
:li.
"OS/2 kernel" object&colon. "Syslevels" page never displayed
TCP/IP data, fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
"Keyboard" object&colon. "Hotkeys" page never used 8&per.Helv
font if enabled&per. Fixed by Paul Ratcliffe&per. 
.br
:li.
Status bars&colon. "Undo" on status bars page 2 in "Workplace
Shell" didn't undo everything&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Hook&colon. This allowed many things during lockup that
weren't supposed to happen, such as opening hot corner
objects&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
XPager&colon. I added a mutex around a global hook flag
which is used by XPager to avoid recursing into the
hook&per. It looks like this has improved the XPager
hangs that occured sporadically when many windows were
opened and closed&per. I am not sure yet if this completely
fixed the problem&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Widget settings management crashed sometimes
in an endless loop when freeing settings data&per. Fixed
by Paul Ratcliffe&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Widget properties dialogs never worked
for subwidgets in a tray&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. If XCenter was on top of screen, menus
weren't displayed in the proper direction&per. Fixed
for object buttons and X-button by Martin Lafaix&per.

.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. MB2 context menu on border or sizing
bar broke with 0&per.9&per.13&per. Fixed by Martin Lafaix&per.

.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Pulse widget broke with some recent version
on some system, causing crashes&per. Fixed, hopefully&per.

.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Trays sometimes lost their current tray
between restarts&per. Fixed&per. 
:eul.
:p.

.* Source file: "vers_2history86_0_9_13.html"
:h2 res=10111 x=right width=70%.XWorkplace 0.9.13
:p.
:hp2.XWorkplace 0&per.9&per.13 (July 6, 2001):ehp2. 
:p.
New features&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
XCenter&colon. Added tray widgets, per popular request&per.
Drag'n'drop doesn't quite work yet though&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Added "Spacing lines" setting to XCenter
view styles&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Added drop support and in-use emphasis
to object button widgets&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Added detailed system information to
tooltips for pulse and sentinel widgets&per. 
.br
:li.
OS/2 Kernel&colon. Added new :font facename='Courier' size=18x12.CONFIG&per.SYS:font facename=default size=0x0. memory settings
to "Memory" page&per. 
.br
:li.
OS/2 Kernel&colon. Added support for driver dialog plugin
DLLs&per. Configuration dialogs can now be added as
plugin DLL to the plugins\drvdlgs directory without
having to modify the XWorkplace sources&per. 
.br
:li.
OS/2 Kernel&colon. Added a new JFS&per.IFS dialog while
I was at it&per. 
:eul.
:p.
Miscellaneous changes&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
General&colon. All XWP message boxes now use the new
shared code that was developed for WarpIN&per. Looks
a bit nicer, in my view&per. 
.br
:li.
General&colon. Did quite a major overhaul of the documentation&per.
Much information was moved from the User Guide to the
various help pages that appear if you press "Help" in
an object settings notebook&per. I find this more helpful
because then the help is in the context of what you're
doing&per. Also added more general explanations of some
OS/2 and WPS concepts to the help file&per. 
.br
:li.
Removed the temporary archive marker file that was previously
used to check for whether a WPS archive was just restored&per.
Thanks, Stefan Milcke&per. 
.br
:li.
"Sort" menu&colon. Per popular request, the menu is
dismissed again, unless shift is held down while clicking
or "always sort" or "folders first" were clicked on&per.

.br
:li.
"Multimedia" object&colon. Device detection on page
1 was completely rewritten&per. Hopefully this fixes
the system hangs some people experienced with buggy
multimedia drivers&per. While I was at it, I added lots
of information to the display&per. 
.br
:li.
Font sample view&colon. default window size was a bit
small&per. Fixed, now using almost the whole screen&per.

.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Made some xwplog&per.log messages more
verbose&per. 
:eul.
:p.
Bugfixes&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
General&colon. Added lots of new checks for audio CDs
in the library code&per. This should finally prevent
the stupid white error boxes on Desktop startup, with
the status bars in the "Drives" folder, and on disk
double-clicks if an audio CD was inserted in a CD-ROM
drive&per. 
.br
:li.
General&colon. Replaced internal binary tree implementation
with a new one&per. The old one proved to balance wrongly
if a certain tree size was reached&per. This should
fix the "Object count mismatch" messages in xwplog&per.log
on shutdown, among other things&per. 
.br
:li.
"Sort" menu&colon. Fixed confusion with check marks
in certain situations&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. "Add widget" menu never worked with sliding
menus enabled&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Paul Ratcliffe fixed the context menu
font&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Fixed a memory leak on widget destruction&per.

.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Tooltips weren't managed properly for
widgets that were just created or destroyed by the user&per.
Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Fixed minor pointer change problem while
settings dialog was displayed&per. 
.br
:li.
System sounds&colon. Changes in 0&per.9&per.13 caused
Win-OS/2 to complain that sound device was busy&per.
Fixed, hopefully&per. 
.br
:li.
"Snap to grid" page&colon. Values for Y origin and Y
spacing were confused&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Boot logos&colon. "Undo" button on "Startup" page in
desktop's settings notebook never restored the boot
logo file setting, which could lead to trouble if your
boss came into the office&per. Fixed; thanks, Steve
Wendt, for pointing this out&per. 
.br
:li.
XShutdown&colon. daemon crashed during shutdown if hook
wasn't active&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
XShutdown&colon. 0&per.9&per.12 code broke WM_SAVEAPPLICATION
behavior for some apps&per. Fixed; went back to pre-0&per.9&per.12
code there&per. 
.br
:li.
XShutdown&colon. Shutdown thread kept marching even
if an exception was currently being processed on another
thread, which prevented the trap logs from being written&per.
Fixed, shutdown thread is now waiting if an exception
handler is running somewhere&per. 
.br
:li.
XShutdown&colon. Shutdown folder carried "Startup folder"
in its progress window title&per. Fixed&per. 
:eul.
:p.

.* Source file: "vers_2history87_0_9_12.html"
:h2 res=10112 x=right width=70%.XWorkplace 0.9.12
:p.
:hp2.XWorkplace 0&per.9&per.12 (June 3, 2001):ehp2. 
:p.
New features&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
Extended associations can now be imported/exported through
an XML file&per. 
.br
:li.
XFolder&colon. Added default folder view override to
"View" page in "Workplace Shell" to prevent inheriting
the default view from the parent folder&per. 
.br
:li.
XFolder&colon. Folder sorting was mostly rewritten&per.
This now finally supports non-default sort classes (e&per.g&per.
in the trash can, which can finally be sorted now too)&per.
Also added "Folders first" as an additional sort setting
to be applied on top of the standard criterion&per.

.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. added "lockup" to X-button menu&per.

.br
:li.
XWPString&colon. added setup string support&per. 
.br
:li.
General&colon. XWP can now read extended BLDLEVEL information,
as used by most of the IBM networking software&per.
Reworked the "Module" page in XWPProgramFile for displaying
additional data, if available&per. We also support NOSTUB
executables now (e&per.g&per. JFS&per.IFS)&per. 
.br
:li.
General&colon. Added "Fix class titles" feature to "XWorkplace
setup"&per. 
.br
:li.
"OS/2 Kernel"&colon. Reworked network drivers, Paul
Ratcliffe added new driver descriptions&per. 
:eul.
:p.
Miscellaneous changes&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
General&colon. Reworked trap logs a bit for more lucid
output&per. Added seg&colon.ofs translation of trapping
CS&colon.EIP for each stack frame&per. 
.br
:li.
General&colon. Sped up XFLDR&per.DLL loading by removing
a lot of fixup relocation records&per. 
.br
:li.
Removed "Partitions" view from WPDrives, which never
worked right&per. 
.br
:li.
Startup&colon. completely rewrote the entire startup
processing to use a separate thread now&per. This should
fix some of the problems on startup, like endlessly
looping startup folders, I hope&per. At least it makes
the code much more readable&per. 
.br
:li.
Folder auto-refresh&colon. reworked quite a bit, this
now picks up file rename too and refreshes the entire
folder if an overflow occured&per. Also fixed some crashes
and locks on the way&per. 
.br
:li.
Function keys&colon. removed "Modifier" setting, since
it did nothing in the first place&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Winlist widget filters now match the
first characters only&per. 
:eul.
:p.
Bugfixes&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
General&colon. Added mutex protection to tooltips, which
should fix some strange problems&per. Also fixed some
other minor problems&per. 
.br
:li.
General&colon. Paul Ratcliffe fixed the ugly line break
display in a number of places&per. 
.br
:li.
General&colon. Chart control (used on XFldDisk "Details"
page) caused huge PM resource leaks which could lead
to system hangs&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
General&colon. Fixed three minor memory leaks&per. 
.br
:li.
XFolder&colon. Disabled "Cleanup INI files" for now&per.
Did more harm than good&per. 
.br
:li.
XFolder&colon. Replacement "File exists" dialog never
populated the target folder, which could lead to duplicate
objects and even system hangs&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
XFolder&colon. "Snap to grid" item on "XFolder" page
didn't work&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
XFolder&colon. Extended menu items in "View" pulldown
broke somehow&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
XFldDisk&colon. "Details" page always displayed 512
bytes for the sector size&per. Fixed, this now _really_
displays the sector size&per. 
.br
:li.
Extended file types&colon. Removing an association or
type on program/file settings notebook pages caused
a trap&per. Fixed&per. Also fixed a small memory leak&per.

.br
:li.
"Workplace Shell"&colon. "Undo" never really worked
on the "Sort" page&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
"OS/2 Kernel"&colon. "Drivers" page frequently displayed
garbage for the driver info&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
"OS/2 Kernel"&colon. HPFS and HPFS386 dialogs crashed
if no parameters existed in :font facename='Courier' size=18x12.CONFIG&per.SYS:font facename=default size=0x0.&per. Fixed,
thanks Lars Erdmann&per. 
.br
:li.
"OS/2 Kernel"&colon. HPFS386 dialog displayed nothing
if HPFS386&per.INI wasn't explicitly given on the IFS
line in :font facename='Courier' size=18x12.CONFIG&per.SYS:font facename=default size=0x0.&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
"OS/2 Kernel"&colon. Fixed another quirk in the :font facename='Courier' size=18x12.CONFIG&per.SYS:font facename=default size=0x0.
routines which caused the wrong line to be replaced
in rare cases&per. 
.br
:li.
Trash can wasn't very good at setting meaningful drive
support defaults&per. Fixed; per default drives are
supported only if they are FAT, HPFS, JFS, or FAT32&per.

.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Added mutex protection to the internal
timers to prevent some race conditions&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Winlist widget now shows hidden windows
on click&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Winlist widget filter changes weren't
picked up any longer since the changes in 0&per.9&per.11&per.
Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Pulse widget didn't update display if
some app occupied the SIQ&per. Fixed; a separate thread
now gets the performance data from OS/2 kernel&per.

.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Trapped sometimes when several threads
attempted to load the widget classes&per. Fixed, added
mutex protection to DLL loading&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Added extra checks for view creation/destruction&per.

.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Fixed crash in tmrTimerTick when animations
were enabled&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. Hopefully fixed hang on XShutdown&per.

.br
:li.
XCenter&colon. X-Button started shutdown/restart Desktop
etc&per. on XCenter thread&per. Fixed, now started on
thread 1&per. 
.br
:li.
XPager&colon. reworked internal mutex handling some&per.
This seems to fix some of the strange PM hangs that
occured sporadically&per. 
.br
:li.
Hook&colon. Martin Lafaix fixed the new sliding menus
mechanism introduced with V0&per.9&per.11&per. Pulldowns
are no longer delayed, and all submenu selections should
be properly processed now (except for some Netscape
submenus, but that's a minor annoyance)&per. 
.br
:li.
XShutdown&colon. Animations frequently didn't show&per.
Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
XShutdown&colon. Now recovering all windows from other
desktops to screen before closing windows&per. 
.br
:li.
XShutdown&colon. Fixed shutdown folder which never waited
for objects to close&per. 
:eul.
:p.

.* Source file: "vers_2history88_0_9_11.html"
:h2 res=10113 x=right width=70%.XWorkplace 0.9.11
:p.
:hp2.XWorkplace 0&per.9&per.11 (April 26, 2001):ehp2. 
:p.
New features&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
The XPager window can now be dragged itself if the drag
starts on an empty space in the pager itself&per. 
.br
:li.
Added XPager context menu&per. 
.br
:li.
Added new :link reftype=hd res=10006.status bar codes&colon.:elink. $zb etc&per. for total
disk size, $L for disk label&per. 
.br
:li.
Really added diskfree widget to the distribution this
time&per. 
.br
:li.
Made Health widget a separate package in the distribution&per.

.br
:li.
Widgets can now be deleted from "Widgets" page in XCenter
settings notebook&per. Properties dialogs can be opened
from there too, but this has not been extensively tested
yet&per. 
:eul.
:p.
Miscellaneous changes&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
Christian Langanke added 16x16 resolutions to the default
replacement icons&per. 
.br
:li.
Optimized the status bar text composition routines for
speed&per. 
.br
:li.
Rewrote large parts of the window list widget&per. This
now displays the buttons in the proper order (new windows
appear to the right)&per. Besides, restoring to maximized
should now work for all session types&per. 
.br
:li.
Added termination exception handler to XWPDAEMN&per.EXE
for proper hook cleanup, should the daemon get killed
for any reason&per. 
.br
:li.
Changed default widget menu item IDs to above 0x7f00
to avoid conflicts with WPS menu item IDs&per. I hope
this won't break any existing widgets&per. 
:eul.
:p.
Bugfixes&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
Config&per.sys routines never found lines that had leading
spaces&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Added an extra check for floppies in the routines that
checked for whether a drive is ready&per. Maybe this
fixes hangs with non-DOS disks&per. 
.br
:li.
Removed useless shadow populate for internal "populate
folders only" call, which was used from, among other
places, the trash can routines&per. 
.br
:li.
Toggling the folder status bar state via the "View"
context menu rarely saved the change&per. Fixed&per.

.br
:li.
Removed a number of useless settings pages for DLL and
driver files&per. 
.br
:li.
Opening objects from the XCenter made them run on the
XCenter thread, which caused a forced close when the
XCenter thread terminated (because the XCenter was closed)&per.
Fixed; now routing all open requests to thread 1&per.

.br
:li.
XCenter "Run" command couldn't handle parameters and
fully qualified executables&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter "Run" entry fields were limited to 30 some characters&per.
Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Standard widget menu items ("Remove", "Help") never
worked for object button widgets&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
"Immediate hilite" handling for sliding menus was completely
rewritten&per. Works much better now&per. 
.br
:li.
Killing XWPDAEMN&per.EXE would only work about a dozen
times before hanging the system for good&per. Added
thread-granular termination handling now, which should
properly clean up now (still looks like a PM bug for
me)&per. 
.br
:li.
XPager "Sticky" page in "Screen" object listed invisible
switchlist entries&per. Fixed, only listing visible
ones now&per. 
.br
:li.
New XShutdown save-object routines from V0&per.9&per.8
attempted to save objects which no longer existed, which
could hang shutdown in certain situations&per. Fixed&per.

.br
:li.
XShutdown hung the system if print jobs were still pending&per.
Fixed; XShutdown will now simply tell the user to remove
those first&per. 
:eul.
:p.

.* Source file: "vers_2history89_0_9_10.html"
:h2 res=10114 x=right width=70%.XWorkplace 0.9.10
:p.
:hp2.XWorkplace 0&per.9&per.10 (April 16, 2001):ehp2. 
:p.
Bugfixes&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
Fixed an ugly memory management bug which caused the
internal DosQProcStat wrappers to trap on some systems&per.&per.&per.
This was mostly seen on the "Threads" page in XWPSetup&per.

.br
:li.
"Modules" page displayed nothing for some exports with
names > 127 chars&per. Also added some support for
Windows executables&per. 
.br
:li.
Enabling the trash can on the XWPSetup "Features" page
caused the font folder to be created&per. Fixed&per.

.br
:li.
XPager no longer recognized the Desktop on some systems&per.
Fixed, I hope&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter tooltips never appeared on systems where Styler/2
was installed&per. Implemented a fix suggested by Alessandro
Cantatore&per. 
.br
:li.
System sounds page didn't work if MMPM/2 wasn't installed
in ?&colon.\MMOS2&per. Fixed, I hope&per. 
:eul.
:p.

.* Source file: "vers_2history90_0_9_9.html"
:h2 res=10115 x=right width=70%.XWorkplace 0.9.9
:p.
:hp2.XWorkplace 0&per.9&per.9 (April 8, 2001):ehp2. 
:p.
New features&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
Added detailed :link reftype=hd res=10020.documentation for XCenter plugins:elink. plus
the "toolkit" directory with the binary release&per.

.br
:li.
Added replacement :link reftype=hd res=10063.folder auto-refresh:elink.&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter remembers fonts and colors for main XCenter
painting also&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenters can be enlarged vertically now with the mouse&per.

.br
:li.
Widgets can now be dragged within their XCenter to allow
reordering them&per. 
.br
:li.
Added delay setting for XCenter auto-hide&per. 
.br
:li.
"Pulse" widget now displays IRQ load as well&per. 
.br
:li.
Added "Sentinel" widget&per. 
.br
:li.
fonz contributed the "Disk Usage" widget&per. 
.br
:li.
Stefan Milcke contributed the "Health" widget&per. 
.br
:li.
Object button widgets can display WPS context menus
now&per.&per.&per. sort of&per. 
.br
:li.
Added "Run" command to X-Button widget&per. 
.br
:li.
Pressing "Shift+Delete" in a folder performs a "true
delete" now, if enabled&per. 
.br
:li.
Added replacement "Types" page for data files, plus
replacement "Associations" page for programs and program
files, which now display the extended file types correctly&per.

.br
:li.
File types can now be renamed on "File types" page in
"Workplace Shell"&per. 
.br
:li.
Added "Unknown only" checkbox to "Import WPS filters"
dialog to hide known WPS filters&per. 
.br
:li.
New settings for MB3 clicks on "Mouse mappings" page
2&per. Thanks, Martin Lafaix&per. 
.br
:li.
MB3 drag scrolling has nice icons and pointers now&per.
Thanks, Martin Lafaix&per. 
.br
:li.
Added "Threads" page to XWPSetup&per. 
.br
:li.
Martin Lafaix added more pages to the settings notebooks
of program files&per. 
.br
:li.
Paul Ratcliffe reworked the startup folders so that
several of them may exist and you can set for each of
them individually whether they should be processed on
each Desktop restart or after bootup only&per. 
.br
:li.
"Partitions" button in XShutdown "Reboot actions" dialog
finally works with LVM too&per. 
.br
:li.
Now allowing XShutdown power-off with APM 1&per.1 also&per.
Use at your own risk; if it ain't working, don't blame
me&per. 
.br
:li.
Fixed xfix, which contained a number of embarrasing
bugs and therefore crashed all the time&per. 
:eul.
:p.
Miscellaneous changes&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
XWorkplace is finally compiled with Pentium optimizations&per.
I had always feared that this would break the code for
386 and 486 processors, but the VAC documentation clearly
says this is not so&per. If this information is incorrect,
please notify me, if you can still reach your system&per.

.br
:li.
Reworked WarpIN installation so that class registration
and object creation is deferred until the Desktop restarts&per.
This should fix the various upgrade problems many people
had&per. Besides, WarpIN supports uninstalling programs
now, so the XWorkplace objects can now be deleted on
uninstall too&per. XWorkplace now requires WarpIN V0&per.9&per.9
though&per. 
.br
:li.
Worked some more on the standard XCenter widgets&per.

.br
:li.
Moved "Screen corners" page from XWPMouse to XWPScreen,
where it seems more logical&per. 
.br
:li.
Reworked XPager settings pages in XWPScreen&per. Thanks,
Martin Lafaix&per. 
.br
:li.
Per popular request, the "Duplicates" window on the
"System paths" page in "OS/2 Kernel" is now non-modal&per.
Besides, an "Edit" button and more system paths have
been added&per. Thanks, Paul Ratcliffe&per. 
.br
:li.
Reworked the trash can to use a mappings file for the
hidden subdirectories of the "\TRASH" directories on
each drive&per. This should finally solve the problems
with the "File exists" dialog popping up all the time&per.
Besides, this should avoid the excessive creation of
WPS file handles that used to occur for the "deep paths"
that were used earlier&per. 
.br
:li.
:hp1.Dramatically:ehp1. sped up trash can populate on first open
after Desktop startup&per. 
.br
:li.
Added several internal caches for the extended data
file associations&per. This :hp1.dramatically:ehp1. speeds up populating
folders with many files&per. Looks like the extended
file assocs are now even faster than the standard WPS
assocs&per. 
.br
:li.
Auto-hide mouse in the XWP hook now reacts to mouse
clicks too&per. 
.br
:li.
The XWP hook now allows multiple objects on the same
hotkey&per. If you have found out how to do it, go ahead&per.
Otherwise don't&per. Thanks, Paul Ratcliffe&per. 
.br
:li.
Changed the prototype for the "init" export of XCenter
plug-in DLLs so that widgets can easily know about their
own HMODULE&per. 
.br
:li.
Font settings weren't respected by "Import WPS filters"
dialog&per. 
.br
:li.
Further optimized string routines&per. 
.br
:li.
Reworked large parts of XShutdown to get rid of several
race conditions and improper sequencing between the
two shutdown threads&per. Also, the saving of Desktop
objects was reworked because the old routines simply
dumped all abstracts to disk&per.&per.&per. which excluded
non-folders that had changes pending in the WPS background
threads&per. All such pending changes should now be
properly detected&per. 
:eul.
:p.
Bugfixes&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
Fixed problems if the trash can did not have the <XWP_TRASHCAN>
ID&per. 
.br
:li.
Fixed a problem with internal list notifications on
object delete&per. Thanks, Martin Lafaix&per. Optimized
lists also to cause less INI accesses&per. 
.br
:li.
Deleting the font folder or trash can caused hundreds
of stupid WPS "cannot delete object" message boxes to
pop up&per. Oh my, this infinite wisdom of the WPS&per.
Fixed, the transient objects are now quietly nuked&per.

.br
:li.
"Delete" from folder menu bar crashed&per. Fixed by
Paul Ratcliffe&per. 
.br
:li.
Global "Menu bar" setting in folder "View" submenu was
sometimes queried wrong&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Fixed (I hope) infinitely growing swapper with XWorkplace
"Create another" menu items from config folder (as mentioned
in readme for quite a while)&per.&per.&per. I tested
this and it appears to work now&per. 
.br
:li.
Deleting the config folder would sometimes lead to WPS
crashes&per. Should be fixed now; added another mutex
for protecting the config folder cache&per. 
.br
:li.
Fixed problems with XCenter closing on shutdown and
Desktop restart&per. This was several problems actually&per.&per.&per.
a race condition during XShutdown, and improper thread
termination with the timers&per. The separate timer
thread has been removed&per. 
.br
:li.
Dragging objects on XCenter bar caused them to always
appear on the left&per. Fixed, they are now properly
added to the right&per. 
.br
:li.
XCenter settings view sometimes appeared on the XCenter
view thread, which wasn't such a good idea&per. This
is now redirected to thread 1&per. 
.br
:li.
Some XCenter default values were reported wrong in its
setup string&per. Fixed by Paul Ratcliffe&per. 
.br
:li.
Widgets drag'n'drop on "Widgets" settings page got badly
confused with the widget order at times&per. Fixed&per.

.br
:li.
"Pulse" widget broke CPU counters on close&per. Fixed&per.

.br
:li.
"Undo" and "Default" on XCenter settings pages never
worked&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
"Undo" and "Default" also had problems on several hook-related
pages&per. Fixed by Martin Lafaix&per. 
.br
:li.
Fixed object hotkey entry fields so that "Set" and "Clear"
can still be accessed with the keyboard&per. Made "Folder
hotkeys" page behave like "Object" page&per. 
.br
:li.
Object count on "Status" page in XWPSetup went below
zero sometimes&per. Fixed by Paul Ratcliffe&per. 
.br
:li.
Sliding menus sometimes caused a flickering focus if
delay was enabled and user clicked on menu item before
delay elapsed&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Fixed "conditional cascade sensitivity" for sliding
menus to always hilite the menu item but only open the
submenu if mouse is over the menu button&per. 
.br
:li.
Fixed bad system hangs when "File exists" replacement
was enabled&per. This was mostly caused by deadlocks
between several WPS mutexes&per. Also the new dialog
hung the system with certain file names&per. 
.br
:li.
Priority change of the Worker thread never worked if
the Worker message queue got filled with too many messages&per.
Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Completely reworked tracking of awake objects by the
Worker thread&per. All awake objects are now tracked
(check the "Status" page in XWPSetup), and performance
is still much better than previously&per. 
.br
:li.
"Shutdown" etc&per. menu items weren't disabled on XCenter
X-button if shutdown was already running&per. Desktop
"Shutdown" menu item wasn't either if submenu was disabled&per.

:eul.
:p.

.* Source file: "vers_2history91_0_9_8.html"
:h2 res=10116 x=right width=70%.XWorkplace 0.9.8
:p.
:hp2.XWorkplace 0&per.9&per.8 (January 26, 2001):ehp2. 
:p.
New features&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
Added the :link reftype=hd res=10015.XCenter,:elink. a WarpCenter replacement&per. 
.br
:li.
Added more items to the context menus on the "File types"
page in "Workplace Shell"&per. 
.br
:li.
Added "No submenu" setting for "Lock in place" context
menu item ("Workplace Shell", "Context menus" page 3)&per.

.br
:li.
Added "Logoff network now" to desktop's removeable menu
items; shutdown menu items can also be configured more
(desktop settings notebook, "Menu items" page)&per.

.br
:li.
Added "Ignore XCenter" to sliding focus settings ("Mouse",
"Movement")&per. 
.br
:li.
Martin Lafaix contributed the "Resources" page to XWPProgramFile&per.

.br
:li.
Added "Close WarpCenter before Desktop" setting to XShutdown
page in Desktop's settings notebook&per. This now allows
you to tell XWorkplace to leave the WarpCenter alone,
if this lead to scroll bars on the desktop&per. Hope
this helps&per. 
:eul.
:p.
Miscellaneous changes&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
Moved NLS-independent resources to a separate DLL (XWPRES&per.DLL)&per.

.br
:li.
Added more error checking to "Empty trash" on shutdown&per.

.br
:li.
Reworked WPS command interception for file engines command
to avoid duplicate code&per.&per.&per. hope I didn't
break anything&per. 
.br
:li.
Optimized XPager window procedure to use less PM resources&per.
Also improved cache locality&per. 
.br
:li.
Martin Lafaix contributed some patches for the display
of the folder content menus to make them look more like
standard menus&per. Thanks&per. 
.br
:li.
"Object" page is now automatically enabled in XWPSetup
when object hotkeys are enabled&per. Some people had
a hard time finding object hotkeys, Sander&per. ;-)

:eul.
:p.
Bugfixes&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
Reworked mutex semaphore protection all over the place&per.
Maybe the WPS is now less prone to hanging when PMSHELL&per.EXE
is killed&per. 
.br
:li.
Reworked NLS initialization&per. This hung the system
when language DLLs failed to load&per. 
.br
:li.
Fixed crashes when archiving displayed a msgbox after
an archive was restored&per. 
.br
:li.
Fixed two potentially dangerous situations with mutexes
and 1) the shared notebook functions and 2) the worker
thread/awake objects registry&per. This could have lead
to system hangs, and maybe it did somewhere&per. 
.br
:li.
Reworked internal timer functions&per. These stopped
working when the date changed&per. 
.br
:li.
Fixed crashes in Worker thread when kernel globals were
locked&per. 
.br
:li.
Added more error checking to internal EA functions&per.

.br
:li.
Changed a USHORT to a ULONG in my internal EXE structures&per.
This _might_ fix problems with very strange and rare
EXE files on the "Modules" page&per. Thanks, Martin
Lafaix, for pointing this out&per. 
.br
:li.
Fixed crashes when favorite or quick-open folders were
deleted&per. 
.br
:li.
Extended folder sorting was pretty broken&per. Dunno
when these bugs were introduced, but open folders did
_not_ react when global sort settings were changed&per.
This was a collection of at least three bugs, which
are fixed now&per. Unfortunately, to fix this, I had
to break the folder sort settings in each folder's extended
attributes, so you will lose all your folder sort settings
with this release&per. Sorry&per. 
.br
:li.
Extended associations didn't work when a data file had
spaces in its full path&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Extended associations ignored program object settings
for "no auto-close after exit" and "minimized"&per.
Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Extended associations did not setup up the program's
environment properly (WP_OBJHANDLE, WORKPLACE__PROCESS),
which broke DragText&per. Thanks, Rich Walsh, for pointing
this out to me&per. 
.br
:li.
Extended associations used "plain text" as the standard
file type for associations always, giving all data files
the icon for plain text associations&per.&per.&per.
removed that&per. 
.br
:li.
"File types" page crashed when a file type was dropped
on one of its descendant file types&per. Fixed, this
is prevented now&per. Thanks, Martin Lafaix&per. 
.br
:li.
On "File types" page, pickup and drop would not work
with the context menu&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Creating a root file type on the "File types" page led
to an error message, even though the file type was created&per.
Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Fixed memory leaks with "File types" page&per. Thanks,
Martin Lafaix&per. 
.br
:li.
Some "Delete" commands would not be intercepted to go
to the trash can if the command was selected from an
object that was not in a folder&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Trash can would sometimes display wrong empty/non-empty
icon after Desktop startup&per. Should be fixed now&per.

.br
:li.
On some systems the trash can folder would appear as
a template in the "Templates" folder&per. Preventing
template creation now&per. 
.br
:li.
Fixed a memory leak with every time an application was
opened via object hotkeys&per. 
.br
:li.
XWPString would never save the "Confirm" setting&per.
Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Extended system sounds broke completely with V0&per.9&per.6&per.
Fixed&per. Duh&per. 
.br
:li.
Pages in "Multimedia" hung the system if the object
was closed while the data was still being inserted by
the background threads&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
XPager has been rewritten in considerable parts&per.
We are now using a linked list instead of a global array
for the internal window list; wrong sticky windows (newly
created ones, Odin and EPM windows) have been fixed;
maximized window handling has been redone&per. Dmitry
Kubov helped doing all this -- thanks very much, Dmitry&per.

.br
:li.
XPager "move thread" now has a higher priority&per.
This should fix problems during desktop switches when
other processes hog the CPU&per. 
.br
:li.
XShutdown would sometimes crash if "Empty trash" was
enabled&per. Fixed&per. 
:eul.
:p.

.* Source file: "vers_2history92_0_9_7.html"
:h2 res=10117 x=right width=70%.XWorkplace 0.9.7
:p.
:hp2.XWorkplace 0&per.9&per.7 (January 26, 2001):ehp2. 
:p.
V0&per.9&per.7 was never officially released, but since
some people got hold of it anyway, that version number
was skipped to avoid confusion&per. 
.* Source file: "vers_2history93_0_9_6.html"
:h2 res=10118 x=right width=70%.XWorkplace 0.9.6
:p.
:hp2.XWorkplace 0&per.9&per.6 (November 25, 2000):ehp2. 
:p.
New features&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
Added QUICKOPEN=IMMEDIATE :link reftype=hd res=10146.setup string:elink. for folders&per.

.br
:li.
Added new :link reftype=hd res=10006.status bar codes:elink. for automatic unit selection
depending on the size of the data displayed&per. Thanks,
Paul Ratcliffe&per. 
.br
:li.
:link reftype=hd res=10060.Extended file associations:elink. should pretty much work now
as designed&per. I had to recreate the entire "start
program" mechanism in the WPS to get this to work since
IBM didn't care to export that&per. Besides I reworked
the internal association mechanisms to use less memory
now&per. Still, all this is a bit slower&per.&per.&per.

.br
:li.
XWPString confirmations and drag'n'drop work now, even
with multiple objects&per. 
.br
:li.
Added logo page to XWPSetup&per. 
.br
:li.
"File types" page in "Workplace Shell" is resizeable
now as well&per. 
.br
:li.
Added method tokens to method tables in "WPS Class List"
object, if anybody cares&per. 
.br
:li.
Added program data to "Object" page&per. 
.br
:li.
Added "conditional cascade sensitivity" to sliding menus
in "Mouse movement" settings ("Mouse" object)&per. Thanks,
Paul Ratcliffe&per. 
.br
:li.
Added more WPS class descriptions&per. 
:eul.
:p.
Miscellaneous changes&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
Reworked the internal string routines to use less heap
allocations&per. This might make a few functions, including
status bars, faster&per. 
.br
:li.
Added description of "Sliding menus" to User Guide,
which was missing&per. 
:eul.
:p.
Bugfixes&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
XWorkplace tended to create lots of invisible menu windows
which were never destroyed&per. Fixed that all over
the place, thus reducing the pressure on PM&per. 
.br
:li.
Some private PM messages had duplicate values&per. Fixed&per.

.br
:li.
Fixed a couple of minor memory leaks&per. 
.br
:li.
"Refresh now" from main menu messed up icon positions&per.
Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Fixed a refresh problems with status bars&per. Also,
the total object count should now always be correct&per.
Fixed by Paul Ratcliffe&per. 
.br
:li.
Greatly reduced memory consumption of the trash can
when deleting large folder trees&per. This should also
put much less stress on the internal Desktop object
management and greatly speed up deleting&per. 
.br
:li.
Trash can didn't respect number settings from "Country"
object&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
"Orphaned classes" in "WPS Class List" had "Create object"
item&per. That didn't make too much sense&per. Fixed
by Paul Ratcliffe&per. 
.br
:li.
Fixed a minor description parsing problem in "WPS Class
List"&per. 
.br
:li.
Added "Refresh now" to "WPS Class List"&per. Thanks,
John Small&per. 
.br
:li.
Fixed close behavior of "Import WPS filters" dialog
on extended "File types" page in "Workplace Shell"&per.

.br
:li.
"Sound" object should work now even if MMPM/2 is installed
on a drive other than the boot drive&per. 
.br
:li.
"Sliding menus" sometimes did not un-hilite items properly,
and submenus sometimes opened more than they should&per.
Fixed by Paul Ratcliffe&per. 
.br
:li.
Object hotkeys stopped working after lockup&per. Fixed
by Paul Ratcliffe&per. 
.br
:li.
Fixed WPS desktop dragging with XPager&per. 
.br
:li.
On startup, XPager now always selects the upper left
desktop correctly&per. 
.br
:li.
"Close VIO" confirmation dialog during XShutdown had
wrong help panel&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
V0&per.9&per.5's XShutdown got stuck closing WarpCenter&per.
Fixed&per. 
:eul.
:p.

.* Source file: "vers_2history94_0_9_5.html"
:h2 res=10119 x=right width=70%.XWorkplace 0.9.5
:p.
:hp2.XWorkplace 0&per.9&per.5 (October 7, 2000):ehp2. 
:p.
New features&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
New XWorkplace logo&per. 
.br
:li.
Added "Dereference shadows" setting to status bars page
2 even when multiple objects are selected&per. 
.br
:li.
Added HPFS386 driver configuration dialog&per. 
.br
:li.
Added flags for APM power-off to :link reftype=hd res=10070.XSHUTDWN&per.EXE:elink.&per.

:eul.
:p.
Miscellaneous changes&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
File operations confirmation windows now use folders
as owner windows&per. 
.br
:li.
Added "Set" button to object hotkeys entry field&per.

.br
:li.
Added a few more help panels&per. 
.br
:li.
Went back to the V0&per.9&per.3 code for closing the
WarpCenter during shutdown&per. 
:eul.
:p.
Bugfixes&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
XWorkplace Installation folder got deleted on every
install, leading to an empty folder on updates&per.
Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
XWPMedia checkbox did nothing in "XWorkplace classes"
dialog (XWPSetup)&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
"Screen" settings notebook was too small when first
opened&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Object setup strings always displayed DEFAULTVIEW=xxx,
even if the class's default view wasn't changed&per.
Fixed&per. Also added DEFAULTVIEW=RUNNING&per. 
.br
:li.
Disk objects had "Create another" menu item&per. Removed
that&per. 
.br
:li.
WPCommandFile had "Module" page inherited from XWPProgramFile&per.
Removed that&per. 
.br
:li.
Fixed progress bar text painting, which was too high
with some resolutions&per. 
.br
:li.
Status bars for WPSharedDir were wrong&per. Fixed by
Paul Ratcliffe&per. 
.br
:li.
Open "WPS class list" got solidly confused when Alt+F4
was pressed&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Orphaned classes in "WPS class list" always had "Deregister"
disabled&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Class list view had "~" character in title&per. Fixed&per.

.br
:li.
Dragging trash objects out of the trash can made them
undeleteable&per. Fixed&per. One of those awful WPS
d'n'd problems&per. 
.br
:li.
Trash can status bars always used "&per." as a thousands
separator&per. Fixed; this respects the "Country" settings
now&per. 
.br
:li.
Trash can never deleted empty hidden "\trash" directories&per.
Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Object hotkeys didn't work after fresh install&per.
Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Sliding focus was always half on, even if disabled,
leading to deactivated windows everywhere&per. Fixed&per.

.br
:li.
Paul Ratcliffe fixed a couple more bugs related to sliding
focus and auto-hide mouse&per. 
.br
:li.
WPS frequently hung after Desktop restart with FP13/14
and WSeB&per. Attempted a fix&per. 
.br
:li.
You have now three options for XShutdown's "save INIs"
behavior&per. Added my own save-INI routines which should
solve the problems which have existed for more than
two years now&per. Thanks, Carsten Arnold, for telling
me about the &per.INI file format&per. 
:eul.
:p.

.* Source file: "vers_2history95_0_9_4.html"
:h2 res=10120 x=right width=70%.XWorkplace 0.9.4
:p.
:hp2.XWorkplace 0&per.9&per.4 (August 9, 2000):ehp2. 
:p.
New features&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
XWorkplace can now resize some settings pages if the
notebook itself is resized&per. 
.br
:li.
Added "Keep original title" to folder instance settings
notebook&per. 
.br
:li.
Added "Initial delay" to startup folder settings notebook&per.
Using sliders for configuration now&per. 
.br
:li.
Added query-setup-strings support for WPProgram&per.

.br
:li.
Added help panels for a number of context menu items
which were missing&per. 
.br
:li.
Added :link reftype=hd res=10054.folder default documents&per.:elink. 
.br
:li.
XWorkplace now creates a marker file called "xwparchv&per.tmp"
on the Desktop before archiving, which is automatically
destroyed again after archiving is complete&per. This
allows for automatic disabling of the archiving functions
if an archive was just restored because then this file
exists&per. This prevents overwriting the most recent
archiving again right after it was restored&per. 
.br
:li.
Trash can icons can be changed the :link reftype=hd res=10014.normal way:elink. now&per.
Replaced "Icon" page for trash can&per. 
.br
:li.
Automatic emptying of trash can before XShutdown works
now&per. The setting has been moved to the "XShutdown"
settings page in the Desktop's settings notebook and
can be overridden in the shutdown confirmation dialog&per.

.br
:li.
Added "Yes to all" message box button for file operations
confirmations&per. 
.br
:li.
Added conversion of MB3 clicks to MB1 double-clicks
("Mouse" objects, "Mappings" page 2)&per. 
.br
:li.
Extended "screen corner objects" to "screen border objects"
so you now have eight objects to be configured (four
corners, four borders)&per. You will need to reconfigure
your objects however&per. 
.br
:li.
Added :link reftype=hd res=10079.XPager sticky windows:elink. settings page to "Screen"
settings object&per. 
.br
:li.
XPager "stay on top" and "flash to top" work now&per.

.br
:li.
Added special XPager treatment for maximized windows&per.

.br
:li.
Added XPager to screen border special functions&per.

:eul.
:p.
Miscellaneous changes&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
Rearranged some of the help pages which had grown too
long&per. 
.br
:li.
Gave XWorkplace installation folder nice icons, finally&per.

.br
:li.
Reworked exception handlers for XWPDAEMN&per.EXE&per.

:eul.
:p.
Bugfixes&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
Archiving wasn't always disabled if "Archiving" flag
was turned off on replacement "Archives" page&per. Fixed&per.

.br
:li.
Display of folder hotkey descriptions in context menu
could not be disabled when folder hotkeys were disabled
altogether in XWPSetup&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
"Refresh now" from main context menu didn't refresh
container&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Fixed separators in WPDataFile context menus&per. 
.br
:li.
"Tree view auto-scroll" had a few repaint problems&per.
Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Clicking "Refresh" on "Object" page doesn't hang WPS
any more&per. 
.br
:li.
Opening "File" page on SWAPPER&per.DAT or CHKDSK&per.LOG
doesn't hang WPS any more&per. 
.br
:li.
Several settings pages had "to be replaced" group titles&per.
Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
"Create object" menu items in XWPSetup remained active
even after objects were created from those menus&per.
Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
"Replace drive not ready" still didn't work with LAN
drives&per. Another fix attempt&per. 
.br
:li.
"Replace file exists" caused dialog to always popup
up with WPS "Create another"&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Trash can "Destroy" always displayed confirmation, even
if turned off&per. 
.br
:li.
Trash can didn't recognize drive Z&colon.&per. Fixed&per.

.br
:li.
Trash can "Drives" page was lacking a help page&per.
Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Multiple selected drives on trash can "Drives" weren't
all moved&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Trash can didn't close open subfolders if the parent
folder was moved to the trash can&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Trash can allowed objects with OBJSTYLE_NODELETE to
be moved to the trash can, including the Desktop itself&per.
Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
File operations (move to trash, true delete) got confused
which objects to operate on when browsing through several
context submenus&per. There's a bug in the WPS which
removes source emphasis on the first WM_ENDMENU which
comes in, even if that applies to a submenu&per. XWorkplace
then thought that source emphasis was set for the entire
folder and worked on that instead&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Removed a debugging error message from file operations,
which displayed a meaningless error code&per. 
.br
:li.
CDFS&per.IFS driver dialog&colon. "Optimize" and "Default"
buttons didn't work&per. Fixed&per. Also added help
page&per. 
.br
:li.
CDFS&per.IFS driver dialog crashed if parameters line
was empty&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
"Backup" and "Undo" buttons didn't work right with new
"Mouse" settings pages&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Help page was wrong in "Edit function key" dialog&per.
Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Special treatment of seamless Win-OS/2 windows with
sliding focus broke with V0&per.9&per.3&per. Fixed&per.

.br
:li.
Seamless Win-OS/2 menus didn't work right with sliding
focus either&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Fixed a few quirks with delayed sliding focus because
timer wasn't stopped in time&per. 
.br
:li.
Sliding menus changed sometimes even if the mouse wasn't
moved&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Desktop context menu with screen borders always popped
up in bottom-left screen corner&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
VIO windows never showed up in the foreground&per. This
was a strange one&per. Fixed that&per. 
.br
:li.
Fixed hangs of MB3 scrolling over Netscape and PMMail&per.

.br
:li.
MB3 features broke compatibility with other PM hooks&per.
Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Fixed "window list as mouse pointer" bug with PMMail&per.

.br
:li.
Fixed a large number of bugs with XPager&per. Toggling
the title bar works now&per. XPager doesn't hang any
more when the boot logo transparent windows are used&per.
XPager's window position is finally saved&per. 
.br
:li.
XShutdown finally detects and closes the WarpCenter
properly&per. This should fix the "desktop icons move"
problem&per. 
.br
:li.
XShutdown created 0-byte INI files without any warnings&per.
Somehow my error handling must have broken with 0&per.9&per.0&per.
This still doesn't fix the "save INIs" problem (see
the :link reftype=hd res=10016.FAQ section:elink.), but at least you get a warning now&per.

.br
:li.
Exception handlers broke again with V0&per.9&per.3&per.
Sigh&per.&per.&per. fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
NetscapeDDE failed when other DDE-aware applications
were running&per. Thanks, Rousseau de Pantalon, for
supplying a fix for this&per. 
:eul.
:p.

.* Source file: "vers_2history96_0_9_3.html"
:h2 res=10121 x=right width=70%.XWorkplace 0.9.3
:p.
:hp2.XWorkplace 0&per.9&per.3 (June 5, 2000):ehp2. 
:p.
New features&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
Added CMDREF&per.INF support to "Drivers" page in "OS/2
Kernel"&per. 
.br
:li.
Added configuration support for original IBM1S506&per.ADD&per.

.br
:li.
Added help to "Drivers" page and IBM1S506&per.ADD/DANIS506&per.ADD
dialog&per. 
.br
:li.
Added "XPager" configuration pages to "Screen" object&per.
Added more colors to be configurable&per. 
.br
:li.
Added :link reftype=hd res=10076."function key" support&per.:elink. 
.br
:li.
Added a new system sound for "hotkey pressed"&per. Found
a nice sound for this in my library too&per. If this
doesn't show up in your "Sound" object, disable and
enable system sounds once in XWPSetup, and answer "Yes"
twice to the questions whether system sounds should
be removed and installed&per. 
.br
:li.
Implemented arrow hotkeys for quick XPager desktop switching&per.

.br
:li.
Added new "Paranoia" setting for disabling the more
advanced XFolder menu functions, in case these still
don't work right somewhere&per. 
.br
:li.
Major rework of the XWP file operations engine&per.
Added "True delete" support (Shift + delete)&per. Proper
error handling and progress display for folders containing
other objects&per. Trash can can finally delete subfolders
with read-only files&per. 
.br
:li.
Implemented confirmations for trash object destruction&per.

.br
:li.
Added error explanation to "Drive not ready" dialog&per.

.br
:li.
Updated bm-lvm&per.cmd by Nenad Milenkovic&per. 
.br
:li.
Shutdown animation can now be enabled for reboots too&per.

:eul.
:p.
Miscellaneous changes&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
Removed "HPFS" page from "OS/2 Kernel" since we have
a "Configure" dialog on the "Drivers" page also&per.

.br
:li.
Made "Syslevels" container a bit larger&per. 
.br
:li.
Folder "BACKGROUND" setup string now returns the boot
drive as "?&colon.\" to make it portable&per. 
.br
:li.
Added better error management to trash can file processing&per.
When deleting files from non-supported drives, you'll
get prompted whether the file should be "really" deleted
instead of just complaining&per. 
.br
:li.
Sped up populating trash can which was kinda slow because
of excessive repaints, especially in Details view&per.

.br
:li.
Reworked multimedia&per. Added new Media thread responsible
for playing sounds and such&per. SOUND&per.DLL is gone,
finally; found a better way of doing this, thanks to
a hint by Achim HasenmÅller&per. 
.br
:li.
Dramatically sped up XPager window movement&per. 
.br
:li.
Moved some more folder message processing code out of
my exception handlers so I don't get blamed for crashes
in the default WPS processing&per. 
.br
:li.
Added SYM parsing in exception handlers for Warp 3 and
Aurora UNI kernels&per. 
.br
:li.
Added new memory heap debugging system for debug builds&per.

:eul.
:p.
Bugfixes&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
Network drives refused to open if "Replace drive not
ready" was enabled&per. Hope to have fixed that now&per.

.br
:li.
Mouse mappings page 2 wasn't showing "Page 2/2"&per.
Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
"WPS Class List" got confused with open windows and
views so that folder views got closed when the class
list view got closed&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Disabling "Snap to grid" in "XWorkplace Setup" had no
effect on context menus&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
ICONSHADOWCOLOR setup string was reported as TREESHADOWCOLOR&per.
Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Completely reworked folder subclassing management (see
src/folder/fdrsubcl&per.c)&per. After two years, I have
finally come up with a new way of storing folder data,
which replaces the old ugly routines which have been
in XFolder/XWorkplace forever&per. I hope this doesn't
conflict with Object Desktop&per. Hope that this fixes
the "no folder close" problem which everybody experiences
irregularily from time to time&per. 
.br
:li.
A timer which was started at Desktop startup was never
stopped&per. Unfortunately, that timer's responsibility
was to destroy the "Archiving" status window&per. Since
the timer kept running, it kept trying to destroy that
window, which resulted in random windows being destroyed
from time to time in the WPS process&per.&per.&per.
fixed that&per. This is maybe the strangest bug I've
ever managed to get into a piece of software, and I
only found it by accident&per. Duh&per. 
.br
:li.
Fixed a few quirks with invisible trash can directory
management&per. Sometimes the trash can left lots of
empty hidden directories on the drives&per. 
.br
:li.
When "Disable startup folder once" was checked in the
"Panic" dialog at startup, the startup folder didn't
even work when the context menu was used&per. Fixed&per.

.br
:li.
Fixed a considerable PM resource leak with bootlogo
bitmaps, which were never deleted after creation&per.

.br
:li.
Fixed a couple of minor memory leaks&per. 
.br
:li.
When a PM hard error window popped up while the startup
folder was being processed, the startup folder would
never disappear, and neither would the boot logo&per.
Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Updating open notebook pages when internal settings
changed wasn't thread-safe&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
"Drivers" page in "OS/2 Kernel" didn't detect non-existent
drivers&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Driver dialog for IBM1S506/DANIS506&per.ADD crashed
if the driver had no parameters at all in :font facename='Courier' size=18x12.CONFIG&per.SYS:font facename=default size=0x0.&per.
Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
DRVF_NOPARAMS broke&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
"Dos window" replacement icon was missing a detail in
32x32 resolution&per. Thanks, Alfredo whatever-your-last-name-is
from Spain, for supplying a replacement&per. 
.br
:li.
"8&per.Helv" font wasn't set right in "Restart Desktop"
confirmation dlg&per. 
.br
:li.
XPager kept appearing in tasklist&per. Fixed that, because
the daemon should not be closed&per. 
.br
:li.
Extended system sounds were played even if disabled
in XWPSetup&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Fixed a few quirks with daemon/hook settings, which
weren't always serialized right&per. 
.br
:li.
Virtual keys (such as function keys) didn't work as
hotkeys in VIO windows&per. For some reason, WM_CHAR
doesn't have the KC_VIRTUALKEY flag set with VIO sessions&per.
Fixed that&per. 
.br
:li.
Mouse pointer was gone forever when hook was uninstalled
while the mouse pointer was hidden&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Fixed the problems with sliding focus combo-boxes closing
all the time&per. 
.br
:li.
Fixed the problems with sliding focus and frames within
frames (VIEW&per.EXE)&per. You can now even slide between
subframes of a main frame&per. ;-) 
.br
:li.
Invoking XShutdown via launch pad broke with V0&per.9&per.0&per.
Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Fixed a few quirks at the end of shutdown, which prevented
the system from displaying the animation and/or end
box right&per. 
:eul.
:p.

.* Source file: "vers_2history97_0_9_2.html"
:h2 res=10122 x=right width=70%.XWorkplace 0.9.2
:p.
:hp2.XWorkplace 0&per.9&per.2 (March 24, 2000):ehp2. 
:p.
New features&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
Incorporated "XPager", virtual desktops&per. 
.br
:li.
Automatic menu selection, even with configurable delay
for submenus (as in Win95)&per. Added second "Movement"
page to "Mouse" object for this&per. 
.br
:li.
New "Screen" settings object, which has those "System"
settings pages dealing with the screen&per. The "Screen"
page from "OS/2 Kernel" has been moved to that object
now&per. 
.br
:li.
Added "Syslevel" page to "OS/2 Kernel"&per. 
.br
:li.
Trash can now automatically calculates the total size
if a folder has been deleted, including subdirectories&per.

.br
:li.
Added meaningful file operations error messages&per.
Drives support is finally respected for deleting objects
to the trash can&per. 
.br
:li.
XSHUTDWN&per.EXE has been added again&per. Seems to
work&per. 
.br
:li.
Added "delay" setting for APM power off to "XShutdown"
page&per. 
.br
:li.
Added hotkey description display in context menus&per.

:eul.
:p.
Miscellaneous changes&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
"Shutdown" menu item now has the "d" shortcut, which
doesn't conflict with "Properties"&per. 
.br
:li.
Further optimized hook logic for speed&per. 
.br
:li.
Changed all XWorkplace object IDs to start with <XWP_xxx>
to avoid conflicts with old XFolder versions&per. 
.br
:li.
The configuration folder is no longer automatically
created at startup because this lead to problems on
some systems&per. Use the "Objects" page in "XWorkplace
setup" to create it manually&per. 
.br
:li.
Updated the "XWorkplace" sub-config folder a bit&per.

.br
:li.
XWorkplace settings objects had a "Create another" menu
item, which doesn't make sense&per. Removed that&per.

.br
:li.
Rearranged controls on "File" page a bit&per. 
.br
:li.
Added "?&colon.\xwplog&per.log" file for XWorkplace
warnings&per. If this file exists, you might have a
problem&per. 
.br
:li.
Increased stack space for all additional XWorkplace
threads&per. 
.br
:li.
Removed context-sensitive help upon pressing F1 on some
notebook pages&per. Now we'll always show the help for
the entire page first&per. 
:eul.
:p.
Bugfixes&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
Warp 3 detection didn't work, leading to wrong default
settings and messy dialogs when XWorkplace was run under
Warp 3&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Fixed a minor notebook mutex error&per. 
.br
:li.
"Archive" status window was displayed even if this was
turned off&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
"Subject" field on first "File" page was limited to
36 characters&per. Changed this to 260, even though
the IBM docs say this isn't so&per. Thanks, Mike Reichel,
for counting the characters&per. 
.br
:li.
Added thread-safety checks to internal folder contents
enumerations&per. 
.br
:li.
With folders, "Object" page would appear between the
two "Icon" pages&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Using work area folders would lock the WPS hard when
objects in the folder were re-opened&per. Fixed&per.

.br
:li.
Removed static view field from folder view structure
(SUBCLASSEDLISTITEM)&per. Now rechecking folder view
every time this is needed because this might change&per.

.br
:li.
Deleting the configuration folder would take to a lot
of WPS-internal crashes the next time a folder context
menu was opened&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Drives were checked for readiness even if "Replace drive
not ready dlg" was disabled&per. Fixed&per. If a drive
cannot be opened now, disable that setting&per. 
.br
:li.
There was a heap allocation error with the XWPSetup
object on object creation, sometimes leading to system
hangs&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
"Features" page "Undo" and "Default" buttons created
duplicate records&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
XFldDisk and XFldShutdown items were checked in the
"XWorkplace classes" dlg even if those classes were
not installed&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Automatically creating the trashcan via "Features" works
now&per. 
.br
:li.
The trash can now displays the "File exists" dialog
correctly when a file exists in the trash can already&per.

.br
:li.
Converting settings from XFolder led to some problems&per.
Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Menu buttons (e&per.g&per. the "Partitions" button)
displayed a menu even if disabled&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
The bitmap which was created with the "Details" chart
was never freed (baaaad PM resource leak)&per. Fixed&per.

.br
:li.
The "Auto-hide mouse pointer" checkbox on the "Mouse
movement" page wasn't working&per. Another (static)
control on the page had the same dialog item ID&per.
%$ı%!, I hate that&per. Took me half an hour to figure
out&per. 
.br
:li.
Mouse-button-3 scrolling didn't work horizontally when
vertical scroll bar was disabled in a window&per. Fixed&per.

.br
:li.
Fixed Netscape hangs with MB3 scrolling when the scroller
changed while being scrolled&per. 
.br
:li.
Fixed some other minor quirks with MB3 scrolling&per.

.br
:li.
Many hook features were triggered even though the mouse
was currently captured by an application or the system&per.
This could lead to severe system hangs, especially with
"show window list everywhere"&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
"Hot corners" desktop menu sometimes conflicted with
"sliding focus" because the focus was immediately given
back to the window under the mouse&per. Fixed&per. 
:eul.
:p.

.* Source file: "vers_2history98_0_9_1.html"
:h2 res=10123 x=right width=70%.XWorkplace 0.9.1
:p.
:hp2.XWorkplace 0&per.9&per.1 (February 18, 2000):ehp2. 
:p.
First XWorkplace public release&per. 
:p.
New features&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
Added object setup string decoding to the "Object" page
of every object's settings notebook&per. 
.br
:li.
Added container view flags to "Object" page details&per.

.br
:li.
New hook features on "Mouse mappings" page 2&colon.
mouse-button-3 scrolling, auto-hide mouse pointers,
and more&per. 
.br
:li.
Added "Show Desktop's context menu" to special functions
with screen corner objects&per. 
.br
:li.
Added "Enable NumLock on Startup" feature&per. 
.br
:li.
Added "Drives" page to trash can's settings notebook
for individual drives support&per. 
.br
:li.
Added second "File" page to file-system objects to display
all extended attributes&per. 
.br
:li.
"WPS Class List" is now multithreaded to some extent&per.

.br
:li.
Trash can "delete" support is finally working! Full
drag'n'drop support also&per. 
.br
:li.
Implemented proper trash can drives support&per. 
.br
:li.
Created generic file operations framework which can
process file operations on the File thread (in order
not to block the user interface)&per. This is now used
for "move to trash can", "restore from trash can", "destroy
trash objects", "empty trash can" -- all multithreaded
and with progress bars&per. 
.br
:li.
"Cannot close VIO window" dialog in XShutdown has been
reworked to store the selection with the auto-close
items list while XShutdown is running&per. 
.br
:li.
Treesize displays the number of files per directory
and can sort according to that now too&per. 
.br
:li.
NetscDDE is now prepared for National Language Support
too&per. 
.br
:li.
Added some SOM kernel classes to "WPS Class List" descriptions&per.

:eul.
:p.
Miscellaneous changes&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
Updated messages for the XFLDTRAP&per.LOG exception
log file&per. 
.br
:li.
Folder content menus are finally limited so that the
menu is not built for several thousand files&per. 
.br
:li.
System sounds are now automatically installed when the
respective flag on the XWPSetup "Features" page is checked&per.

.br
:li.
Added NLS to various parts of XWorkplace where it was
missing&per. 
.br
:li.
Reorganized WPS Class List code again&per. 
.br
:li.
Took the time to work on exception handling once more&per.
Made the entire mechanism more bomb-proof&per. 
:eul.
:p.
Bugfixes&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
After closing a subdialog of a notebook page, the WPS
would sometimes hang&per. Now all subdialogs are owned
by the frame instead of the page, which should fix this,
even though I still don't understand what's going here&per.

.br
:li.
Replaced all DosRequestMutexSem calls with WinRequestMutexSem
calls&per. 
.br
:li.
"Open parent" (Backspace) would crash the WPS when used
in a drive (root folder) window&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
"Open parent and close" (Shift+Backspace per default)
invoked on the Desktop would close the Desktop&per.
Not such a good idea&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
"Select by name" was added for Tree views also, which
didn't make sense&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
WinDestroyWindow was never called on "Select by name"
windows&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Status bars were added to folders even though the feature
was disabled in "Workplace Shell"&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Right-clicking on a status bar would produce the folder's
context menu, but when changing to a different submenu,
the main menu would disappear and the new submenu would
appear just anywhere on the screen&per. I finally figured
out how to call wpDisplayMenu correctly, so this is
fixed now&per. 
.br
:li.
Forgot "Work area" setting on "File" page with folders&per.
Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Fixed a number of small memory leaks with shaped windows,
notebook page management, progress bars, WPS class list,
split window controls, "OS/2 Kernel" object&per. 
.br
:li.
Sometimes invoking settings strings on folders (esp&per.
"ALWAYSSORT") would work initially, but not be saved
to the extended attributes of the folder&per. Fixed&per.
Er, this must have been in XFolder forever&per. 
.br
:li.
Replacement "File exists" dialog would sometimes hang
the WPS if a large number of files was processed&per.
Fixed; now using folder mutex semaphores for thread
safety&per. 
.br
:li.
Trash can kept crashing the WPS in some background thread
a few seconds after the last trash object was destroyed&per.
This happened because the WPS unloaded the XWPTrashObject
class if no more objects of that class existed&per.
Fixed, but that one was tricky&per. 
.br
:li.
Trash objects had "Create another" menu item, which
doesn't make sense&per. Removed&per. 
.br
:li.
Fixed trash can populate/refresh mechanism&per. This
is now faster and doesn't crash all the time (famous
last words)&per. 
.br
:li.
Fixed heap errors with text message file (TMF) handling,
which caused sporadic, non-reproduceable crashes&per.
Also, the TMF got recompiled every single time; fixed
that also&per. 
.br
:li.
Loading and unloading the XWorkplace hook via XWPSetup
didn't work&per. Fixed hookInit and hookKill (xwphook&per.c)&per.

.br
:li.
Fixed XShutdown thread synchronization problems introduced
with V0&per.9&per.0&per. 
.br
:li.
The new XShutdown confirmation introduced with V0&per.9&per.0
wasn't always working right&per. Fixed&per. 
:eul.
:p.

.* Source file: "vers_2history99_0_9_0.html"
:h2 res=10124 x=right width=70%.XWorkplace 0.9.0
:p.
:hp2.XWorkplace 0&per.9&per.0 (November 28, 1999):ehp2. 
:p.
Obviously, I've renamed the whole thing&per. This version
was never released as a binary version, but only uploaded
in source to the Netlabs CVS server&per. 
:p.
New features (lots of major ones)&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
:link reftype=hd res=10082."XWorkplace Setup" object:elink. with more general settings&per.

.br
:li.
Extended association mechanism&per. 
.br
:li.
:link reftype=hd res=10061.XWorkplace trash can&per.:elink. 
.br
:li.
New :link reftype=hd res=10009.XWorkplace PM hook:elink. for mouse and keyboard features
(object hotkeys, sliding focus, screen corner objects)&per.

.br
:li.
The "WPS Class List" has been greatly enhanced&per.
This is now in a separate object, with a split view
for a more lucid display&per. We now have a new "Create
object" context menu item for each installed class,
and method information can be displayed&per. 
.br
:li.
New "Sound" object replacement (by replacing the WPSound
class)&per. This has much better sound selections now,
with full sound scheme support, even on Warp 3&per.

.br
:li.
"System paths" page in "OS/2 Kernel"&per. 
.br
:li.
"Drivers" page in "OS/2 Kernel"&per. 
.br
:li.
"File" pages in file-system object settings notebooks
can be replaced with a new, single page&per. 
.br
:li.
"Details" page in disk objects can also be replaced&per.

.br
:li.
All-new "Module" page in program file settings objects,
which retrieves additional information from the executable
direcly&per. 
.br
:li.
:link reftype=hd res=10045."Select by name" dialog:elink. now has a history of the last
10 file masks which were entered&per. 
.br
:li.
Status bars can now dereference shadows (new setting
in "Workplace Shell")&per. 
.br
:li.
New "Menu bar" setting in Warp 4's "View" context submenu&per.

.br
:li.
New "XWorkplace panic" dialog when Shift key is held
down during Desktop startup, which allows you to selectively
disable XWorkplace features&per. 
.br
:li.
New "Startup" and "Shutdown" pages in Desktop's settings
notebook&per. Startup page allows you to configure the
:link reftype=hd res=10066.boot logo:elink. now&per. There are now two boot logo styles,
for many people preferred the old blow-up style over
the transparent boot logos&per. 
.br
:li.
XFldDesktop can now switch between several shutdown
menu styles&per. Also, "Sort" and "Arrange" can be disabled
for the Desktop only&per. 
.br
:li.
New "Partitions" button in user-reboot items dialog
to automatically add BootManager partitions&per. 
.br
:li.
Per popular request, exception handler beeping can be
disabled now ("XWorkplace Setup", "Paranoia" page)&per.

.br
:li.
Treesize&colon. is now NLS enabled and dynamically updates
the directory sizes even while collecting files (instead
of just displaying "working&per.&per.&per.")&per. 
:eul.
:p.
Miscellaneous changes&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
I've finally found the time to rework all the functions
in the linklist&per.* files&per. This should speed up
a number of internal functions significantly&per. 
.br
:li.
The code for building folder context menus from the
Configuration Folder contents has been mostly rewritten&per.
This now uses less memory and implements a cache for
the objects in the contents folder so that they need
not be rebuilt every time a context menu is opened,
but only if the &per.ICONPOS EAs changed&per. Lots of
new function in menus&per.c for this&per. 
.br
:li.
Restructured settings pages all over the place&per.

.br
:li.
Raised default "variable menu item ID offset" to 700
for :link reftype=hd res=10035.Object Desktop compatibility:elink.&per. 
.br
:li.
Included Christian Langanke's new TMF functions for
message handling&per. XWorkplace message files are now
plain text; MKMSGF&per.EXE is no longer needed to translate
message files&per. 
.br
:li.
Removed the "default class title" for the XFolder class&per.
Folder default titles are no longer changed&per. 
.br
:li.
Improved multithreading all over the place&per. Introduced
new "File" thread with regular priority which takes
over some functionality from the Worker thread&per.

.br
:li.
Also, "Refresh now" now operates in the "File" thread
(which blocked the user interface previously)&per. 
.br
:li.
"File exists" dialog now displays file sizes in bytes,
not KB&per. 
.br
:li.
XShutdown now writes time information into the XSHUTDWN&per.LOG
file with each line&per. 
:eul.
:p.
Bugfixes&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
Fixed a minor problem when NLS strings were not found
(cmnLoadString)&per. 
.br
:li.
Fixed the ancient check box double-click bug&per. ;-)
Double-clicks on check boxes are no longer ignored (fnwpNotebookCommon,
notebook&per.c)&per. 
.br
:li.
Some users reported that the Configuration Folder was
no longer found with certain configurations when it
was moved away from the location where the install program
creates it&per. Fixed; since the WPS method which has
been defined for this doesn't seem to be working with
all Warp versions and fixpak levels (esp&per. not on
Aurora), I have written my own (wpshQueryObjectFromID)&per.

.br
:li.
When folder auto-sort was off but status bars enabled,
folder contents would keep scrolling up when opened
in Icon view, adding ugly scroll bars to the folder
window even if not necessary&per. Fixed (now zeroing
SUBCLASSEDLISTITEM properly, cmnSubclassFolderFrame,
common&per.c)&per. 
.br
:li.
Folder content menus would sometimes crash with titles
> 100 chars&per. 
.br
:li.
"View" pulldown in Warp 4 folder menu bars lacked the
additional items&per. I'm not sure if this was broken
in V0&per.85 already or if I broke this since then,
but it's working now anyway&per. ;-) 
.br
:li.
Right-click on status bars opened the closed-view context
menu (open-view items were missing)&per. Fixed (fnwpStatusBar,
xfldr&per.c)&per. 
.br
:li.
The "Select by name" dialog had problems finding files
according to wildcards like "*html" (without dots)&per.
Fixed (new function strhMatch, stringh&per.c)&per. 
.br
:li.
The boot logo would remain on the screen forever if
startup folder processing was cancelled or errors occured
during startup&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Fixed a few small memory leaks (XFldObject "Object"
settings page, "Auto-close items" and "User reboot"
dialogs)&per. 
.br
:li.
For drives > 4 GB, XFolder still returned garbage status
bar information&per. Fixed, thanks to RÅdiger Ihle who
found the bug in the sources&per. 
.br
:li.
Error message 99 when opening a disk object had a "%1"
string in there&per. Fixed; this now displays the drive
letter&per. 
.br
:li.
The WPS class list produced an exception every time
a class was deregistered using the context menus&per.
Fixed; container record cores are now freed before the
corresponding data is freed&per. 
.br
:li.
Previous versions sometimes forgot to process the contents
of the XWorkplace startup folder upon first bootup&per.
This has been completely reworked, now using the XWorkplace
daemon (XWPDAEMON&per.EXE)&per. 
.br
:li.
XShutdown would crash when the INI file names were specified
in lower case in :font facename='Courier' size=18x12.CONFIG&per.SYS:font facename=default size=0x0.&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
XShutdown sent WM_CLOSE to some applications instead
of just WM_QUIT&per. For example, Program Commander
didn't like this too much&per. Fixed; all PM apps get
WM_QUIT now&per. 
.br
:li.
For some reason, XFldObject&colon.&colon.wpObjectReady
does not get called for WPFolder instances (at least
on my Warp 4 FP 10), so that the Worker thread was unable
to track awake folders&per.Fixed; we now override XFolder&colon.&colon.wpObjectReady
also&per. 
.br
:li.
Finally made the global and kernel settings thread-safe
in really all possible situations (hopefully)&per. This
fixes a number of problems with folder windows which
are not running on thread 1, which happens sometimes
(e&per.g&per. folders opened from REXX or TREESIZE&per.EXE)&per.

.br
:li.
Reworked exception handlers once again&per. This fixes
hangs in the Worker thread when PMSHELL&per.EXE got
killed or trapped somewhere, which used to require a
system reboot&per. 
.br
:li.
I have reorganized large portions of the XShutdown code,
which should help with some hung systems during XShutdown&per.

:eul.
:p.

.* Source file: "vers_2history2.html"
:h2 res=10125 x=right width=70%.XFolder Revision History (before 0.9.0)
:p.
This page lists the changes made to XFolder (before
XWorkplace 0&per.9&per.0 was released) and is identical
to the "Revision history" page of the XFolder V0&per.85
documentation&per. :hp2.
:p.
Version 0&per.85 (March 15, 1999):ehp2. Well, V0&per.84 proved
to have a few more bugs&per. 
:p.
New features&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
Added lots more WPS class descriptions sent in by various
people&per. 
.br
:li.
Replaceable shape window :link reftype=hd res=10066.Desktop start logos&per.:elink. 
:eul.
:p.
Bugfixes&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
Status bar information for program objects failed if
WPProgram class was replaced (e&per.g&per. DTProgram
of DragText)&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Status bars crashed when translating $T key for WPFileSystem
objects, but only in 12-hour time display ("Country"
object)&per. Fixed (strhFileDate, /helpers/stringh&per.c)&per.

.br
:li.
Error message when changing object ID on "Internals"
page had funny title&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
The "lastpid" file was always written to the root dir
of the boot drive instead of XFolder's own "bin" dir&per.
Fixed&per. 
:eul.:hp2.
:p.
Version 0&per.84 (February 4, 1999):ehp2. First non-beta&per.
Hope this works better&per. 
:p.
New features&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
Implemented new drive checking when Disk objects ("root
folders") are opened to avoid the annoying system error
messages of OS/2&per. You'll get a slightly more comfortable
message box now with the default OS/2 SYSxxx error message&per.
That's a bit better, I think&per. 
.br
:li.
Finally, a number of WPS :link reftype=hd res=10014.default icons:elink. can be freely
replaced&per. 
.br
:li.
Status bar support for WPUrl objects; they display the
URL in the status bar per default&per. 
.br
:li.
Double-click on status bar opens folder settings notebook&per.

.br
:li.
:link reftype=hd res=10070.XSHUTDWN&per.EXE:elink. can finally do a Desktop restart too&per.

:eul.
:p.
Miscellaneous changes&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
Reworked thread and exception handling once more&per.
Added exception handling to status bars (fnwpSupplObject,
xfldr&per.c)&per. 
.br
:li.
Reworked the folder subclassing to speed up processing
and added more checks for error conditions (fnwpSubclassedFolderFrame,
xfldr&per.c)&per. 
:eul.
:p.
Bugfixes&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
V0&per.83 reported a wrong version number of itself&per.
Fixed&per. Well, we're at V0&per.84 now anyway&per.

.br
:li.
Removal of context menu items broke for abstract objects
in V0&per.81&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
"File attributes" menu didn't work when several data
files were selected&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Fixed a few keyboard focus problems with status bars&per.

.br
:li.
Also changed the way status bars save whether the size
of a folder window has been increased already&per. This
is now stored together with the other folder pos data
in OS2&per.INI, "PM_Workplace&colon.FolderPos"&per.
The status bar keys end in "@XFSB"&per. This should
fix the problem that folder windows were frequently
too small when folder positions were not properly saved&per.

.br
:li.
When users tried to move the XFolder Configuration Folder,
they got the "Config folder does not exist" message
all the time&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Also, that message is only opened once now&per. 
.br
:li.
Fixed a few problems with the "File exists" dialog&colon.
1) XFolder's "does file exist" algorithm behaved differently
from the default WPS behavior when files were copied
from HPFS to FAT or from FAT to FAT and the long name
was different from the real name; 2) on FAT drives,
the proposed name were in 8+3 format, which is not very
useful; 3) the proposed names used to be based on the
existing real names, not file titles&per. 4) Also, "rename"
behaved funny on FAT drives sometimes&per. Ooouuuargh&per.
Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Folder views behaved really strange with some CD-ROM
directories, especially with the new Joliet support
of CDFS&per.IFS&per. I suspect this was due to some
of my DosDevIOCtl's, which I have removed now&per. 
.br
:li.
On some systems, opening folder content menus for removeable
drives hung the system when those drives were empty
(e&per.g&per. because no floppy disk was in the drive)&per.
Added drive checking for folder content menus&per. 
.br
:li.
In rare occasions, previous versions would mess up the
:font facename='Courier' size=18x12.CONFIG&per.SYS:font facename=default size=0x0. file by not setting the correct file
size after writing, which led to garbage characters
at the end of the file&per. Fixed, thanks to ARAKAWA,
Atshushi&per. 
.br
:li.
The Worker thread was frequently given "regular" priority,
which slowed down the other WPS threads&per. Fixed;
Worker thread priority is now properly set to "idle"&per.

.br
:li.
SOUND&per.DLL was missing in the V0&per.83 distribution&per.
Sorry, fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Playing of system sounds was always interrupted when
a new sound was to be started, even if the new sound
file did not exist&per. Fixed (fntQuickThread, xthreads&per.c)&per.

.br
:li.
XFolder would sometimes fail to process its startup
folders even though it should have processed it&per.
Fixed (fnwpWorkerObject, xfdesk&per.c)&per. 
.br
:li.
In rare occasions, e&per.g&per. with ObjectREXX's WPS
support, saving the WPS objects during shutdown would
crash&per. I've now added even more "quiet" exception
handling, maybe this helps&per. 
:eul.:hp2.
:p.
Version 0&per.83 beta (December 14, 1998):ehp2. Well, the
major rework of V0&per.82 broke a number of things,
so there are more bugfixes here&per. There are still
a couple of known bugs which I haven't had time to fix
yet, but I wanted to get these bugfixes out before Christmas&per.
See "bugs&per.txt" on my homepage for up-to-date info&per.

:p.
New features&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
:link reftype=hd res=10070.XSHUTDWN&per.EXE:elink. now has an option for turning on the
shutdown log&per. 
.br
:li.
BOOTMGR&per.CMD to automatically add user-reboot options&per.
See :link reftype=hd res=10017.Related Files:elink. for more&per. 
:eul.
:p.
Miscellaneous changes&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
Replacement "File conflict" dialog now automatically
selects the filestem in the rename proposals&per. 
.br
:li.
A few cosmetic changes to the XFolder dialogs&per. 
:eul.
:p.
Bugfixes&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
Removal of default menu items broke for data-file objects
in V0&per.81&per. Fixed (new wpFilterPopupMenu in xfdataf&per.*)&per.

.br
:li.
Changing file attributes from shadow context menus led
to crashes when several shadows were selected&per. Fixed
(mnuFileSystemSelectingMenuItem, menus&per.c)&per. 
.br
:li.
Copying file names didn't work right either if this
was selected from a context menu of several shadows&per.
Fixed (same place)&per. 
.br
:li.
Replacement "File conflict" dialog sometimes displayed
outdated file size/date/time information&per. Fixed
(wpConfirmObjectTitle, xfobj&per.c)&per. 
.br
:li.
With V0&per.82, XFolder forgot how to write :font facename='Courier' size=18x12.CONFIG&per.SYS:font facename=default size=0x0.
to disk&per. That rendered the whole "OS/2 Kernel" object
pretty useless&per. Fixed, sorry (fncbConfigItemChanged,
xfsys&per.c)&per. 
.br
:li.
SUPPRESSPOPUPS wasn't properly read from :font facename='Courier' size=18x12.CONFIG&per.SYS:font facename=default size=0x0.
("Errors" page)&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
The second "Screen" page which is inserted into the
"System" object for some video drivers did not appear
in "OS/2 Kernel", but somewhere in "Workplace Shell"&per.
Fixed (wpAddDMQSDisplayTypePage, xfsys&per.*)&per. 
.br
:li.
XShutdown sometimes reported a data size of 0 when saving
INI keys&per. This is now silently ignored, so that
those error messages shouldn't appear any longer&per.

.br
:li.
XShutdown got confused with programs which appeared
with a PROG_DEFAULT type in the tasklist&per. Fixed
(xsdBuildShutList, xfdesk&per.c)&per. 
.br
:li.
APM power-off entered a critical section after calling
the APM interface, which kept power-off from functioning&per.
Fixed (apm&per.c)&per. 
.br
:li.
Dialogs were resized very badly when video resolution
was changed&per. Fixed; I am now using my own routines
for storing/restoring window positions in winh&per.*&per.

.br
:li.
Treesize reportedly had trouble on very large hard drives&per.
I suspect this was due to my use of unsigned int variables,
which can only hold values up to some 4 billion (= 4
GB)&per. Fixed, I'm now always using double variables&per.

:eul.:hp2.
:p.
Version 0&per.82 beta (November 19, 1998):ehp2. This is a
:hp1.major:ehp1. rework&per. It might not look too different from
the previous version, but I've cleaned up a lot of things&per.

:p.
New features&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
More Treesize settings&colon. size display format, low-priority
search&per. 
.br
:li.
XFolder :hp1.finally:ehp1. has OS/2 Warp 4 notebook buttons&per.
There's a new function winhAssertWarp4Notebook in /helpers/winh&per.c
which can do this with any notebook page without having
to change the dialog resources&per. Thanks, Martin Lafaix,
for the necessary information&per. 
.br
:li.
Thanks to ARAKAWA Atsushi, APM power-off now works&per.
(I hope&per. Again, I cannot test this&per.) 
.br
:li.
Added a few more WPS class descriptions&per. 
:eul.
:p.
Miscellaneous changes&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
Removed the XFldFileSystem class because it wasn't doing
much anyway and caused installation failures on Warp
3 without fixpaks&per. Its functionality is now handled
by the XFolder and XFldDataFile classes directly&per.

.br
:li.
Removed the XFolder exit list because this seemed to
have caused some problems during Desktop restarts (xfdesk&per.c)&per.
Also changed the algorithm which determines whether
the startup folder should be processed (fnwpWorkerObject,
xfdesk&per.c)&per. 
.br
:li.
Completely reworked all the settings notebook page logic&per.
Almost all pages are now using much more lucid callbacks
from the new notebook&per.* files&per. This also ensures
proper updating of pages when other pages are currently
open too&per. 
.br
:li.
Completely reworked the SOM logic for the "WPS Classes"
page in "Workplace Shell"&per. Maybe this helps with
the problems previous versions had on some systems&per.
Also, this now even displays classes which do not appear
in the "official" WPS class list, because some internal
classes are loaded independently of that&per. Finally,
multiple class replacements are now properly displayed&per.
Found an interesting undocumented SOM method (see clsWpsClasses2Cnr
in classlist&per.c for details)&per. 
.br
:li.
Also added source emphasis to the "WPS Classes" container
when context menus are opened&per. Previous versions
had trouble keeping the selected classes apart&per.

.br
:li.
XFolder is now smart enough to write changes to :font facename='Courier' size=18x12.CONFIG&per.SYS:font facename=default size=0x0.
in lower case if the keyword which is replaced contains
lower-case characters too (fnwpConfigCommon, xfsys&per.c,
and str* helper functions in /helpers/dosh&per.*)&per.

.br
:li.
Fixed a coupla things with NLS DLL loading to make V0&per.82
work with V0&per.81 NLS DLLs (cmnQueryNLSModuleHandle,
common&per.c)&per. 
.br
:li.
XFolder can now write SUPPRESSPOPUPS=0 on "Errors" page
in "OS/2 Kernel"&per. This is a new setting since FP29
(fnwpConfigCommon, xfsys&per.c)&per. 
.br
:li.
Sped up confirmation dialog display (XFldObject&colon.&colon.wpConfirmObjectTitle,
xfobj&per.c)&per. 
.br
:li.
Treesize is now much faster collecting extended attributes
(up to 300%)&per. Also fixed some strange hangs/crashes
on some directories&per. 
:eul.
:p.
Bugfixes&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
"Templates" checkbox had disappeared from several object
notebooks in V0&per.80 (removed various wpclsQueryStyle
method overrides)&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Previous versions tended to crash if folders were not
running on thread 1 of the WPS&per. This was especially
the case with folders created by various install programs
(StarOffice, IBM feature install)&per. Sorry, XFolder
status bars apparently weren't thread-safe&per. XFolder
now creates a new object window for each folder which
is opened (fnwpSupplObject, xfldr&per.c), so that status
bar manipulation always occurs on the thread in which
the folder is running&per. 
.br
:li.
First "Context menus" settings page had German buttons&per.
This was just an educational measure&per. ;-) Fixed&per.

.br
:li.
"Status bars" page 2 had "XFldDataFile" as the default
class selection, even though that class doesn't support
status bar codes&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Added more error checking to the "QuickOpen" and "Favorite
Folder" functions&per. Maybe this helps with those strange
exceptions on the first settings page for folders&per.

.br
:li.
XFolder now enforces minimum settings notebook sizes
when these are initially opened, because large pages
were truncated previously (new wpclsQuerySettingsPageSize
method overrides in xfdesk&per.* / xfsys&per.*)&per.

.br
:li.
Reworked the "folder content" menu display so that it
only uses regular icons now&per. Maybe this solves the
mysterious crashes with some video drivers&per. 
.br
:li.
Reworked several parts in menu handling because items
were inserted in the wrong places (menus&per.c)&per.
I also forgot to add the "folder view" items to Warp
4's menu bar too&per. And "Create another" was always
disabled, no matter if this was desired in the "Workplace
Shell" object&per. Finally, "Select by name" wouldn't
show up on Warp 3&per. All fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Also added more error checking when evaluating the config
folder&per. This should lead to less warning messages
if objects are deleted from there (menus&per.c)&per.

.br
:li.
Startup/QuickOpen status windows were not destroyed,
but only hidden when that action was finished&per. Fixed&per.

.br
:li.
INI file maintenance broke somewhere in V0&per.8x; this
is now done by the Worker thread (xfdesk&per.c)&per.
Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Saving INIs&colon. "Ignore" button should now work when
errors occur (/helpers/prfh&per.c)&per. 
.br
:li.
Fixed a few repaint problems with progress bars (/helpers/progbars&per.c)&per.

.br
:li.
Fixed a lot of bugs with the new system sounds&per.
For one, XFolder failed to install on systems where
MMPM/2 was not installed, because XFLDR&per.DLL was
linked against the MMPM/2 libraries, which then could
not be imported&per. So we have a new, second SOUND&per.DLL,
which does all the sound playing&per. If loading that
DLL fails, XFolder simply won't play sounds&per. See
the sound&per.* files for details&per. -- Second, XFolder
got really confused playing sounds when other applications
needed the audio device too&per. This is now solved;
XFolder checks for whether the device is available,
and if another application wants the device while XFolder
is playing, playing is stopped also&per. -- Third, System
sounds in V0&per.81 worked only if they had been disabled
and enabled again in the "Sound" object (cmnQuerySystemSound,
common&per.c)&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Couple of broken links in the German HLP file&per. Fixed&per.

.br
:li.
Install script crashed when invalid language code was
entered&per. Fixed&per. 
:eul.:hp2.
:p.
Version 0&per.81 beta (October 18, 1998):ehp2. Starting with
this version, the file and function of the error in
the source files is specified here too&per. For details
about the source code changes, refer to the "CHANGELOG&per.TXT"
file in the source distribution&per. 
:p.
New features&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
Treesize external program&per. Part of the default context
menu now&per. 
.br
:li.
Due to popular request, :link reftype=hd res=10046."Snap to grid":elink. can now snap
the selected icons only&per. 
.br
:li.
The position of the startup folder status window is
finally saved and restored the next time&per. Sorry
this has taken so long&per. 
:eul.
:p.
Miscellaneous changes&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
Gave up using SOM multiple inheritance, which seems
to have caused too much trouble&per. In detail, the
xfSelectingMenu and xf* methods for status bars have
been removed from XFldObject and subclasses&per. Status
bar single-object info is now handled in statbars&per.c
(new file) with _somIsA() calls instead&per. Not as
elegant, but might be a bit faster than SOM method resolution
too&per. 
.br
:li.
XFldProgram class removed&per. Its only purpose was
for status bars using SOM multiple inheritance&per.
Functionality is now handled by menus&per.c&per. 
.br
:li.
Removed extended Settings submenus&per. Caused too much
trouble&per. Instead, you may now set additional "Attributes"
and "Folder view" menu items in "Workplace Shell"&per.

.br
:li.
Improved animation code to avoid flickering&per. All
the common code for this is now in the new animate&per.*
files&per. 
.br
:li.
Added exception handling to "XFolder" notebook page
in folders&per. This seems to have broken on some systems&per.

.br
:li.
Made the file-system class replacements return the CLSSTYLE_NEVERTEMPLATE
from wpclsQueryStyle so that no additional templates
are produced in the Templates folder&per. 
.br
:li.
Reworked status bar code completely&per. Should be quite
a bit faster now; however, each code is only translated
_once_ now&per. 
.br
:li.
Rearranged the pages in the "OS/2 Kernel" and "Workplace
Shell" objects&per. Also changed the replaced SOM methods
(xfsys&per.*)&per. "OS/2 Kernel" should now contain
all the settings which require a reboot to take effect&per.
I guess this is a more logical rule&per. 
.br
:li.
Removed those darn xfclsQueryModule methods which were
used to query the module handle of xfldr&per.dll&per.
This might have caused installation failures on some
systems&per. There is a new DLL init function in module&per.c
now which is a lot faster and causes less problems&per.

.br
:li.
As a nice side-effect to this, XFolder does not need
any INI entries any more to run properly&per. If you
delete the whole "XFolder" INI thing, XFolder will re-initialize
itself&per. 
.br
:li.
Install script set up config folder to open in Tree
view per default&per. Unfortunately this caused &per.LONGNAME
EAs not to be rewritten when the main config folder
was altered&per. Fixed, this now uses non-flowed icon
view&per. 
:eul.
:p.
Bugfixes&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
"HPFS" page wrote "LAZY&colon.1" instead of "/LAZY&colon.1"
to :font facename='Courier' size=18x12.CONFIG&per.SYS:font facename=default size=0x0.&per. Fixed (xfsys&per.c, fnwpConfigCommon)&per.

.br
:li.
"HPFS" page could read a few IFS parameters in upper
case only&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
"Memory" page wrote "HPFS" settings too&per. Forgot
a "break" in fnwpConfigCommon, xfsys&per.c&per. 
.br
:li.
"Errors" page wrote "REIPL=YES" instead of "REIPL=ON"&per.
Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
"Object Internals" page displayed object handles only
25% of the time, depending on how large your object
repository was&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Install script failed to create "Workplace Shell" and
"OS/2 Kernel" objects if the XFolder Configuration folder
already existed&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Creating objects from context menus caused non-reproduceable
system hangs from time to time (really bad ones where
even C-A-D faild)&per. Added more error checking (cmnCreateFromTemplate,
common&per.c; this used to be XFldObject&colon.&colon.xfCreateFromTemplate)
and rewrote large parts of that routine to use container
messaging now instead of WPS methods&per. Seems to always
work now&per. 
.br
:li.
Reworked "Snap to grid" also so that it now properly
uses container messages (xfSnapToGrid, xfldr&per.c)&per.

.br
:li.
Status bars now check for removeable drives before querying
disk information&per. Those ugly "drive not ready" popups
should now be gone&per. 
.br
:li.
Status bars reported garbage if a filename to be displayed
contained a '$' character also&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
"Folder hotkeys" page listed an "Insert" item, which
should have been called "Paste"&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Opening large folder content menus (which were repositioned
on the screen) would sometimes cause all menus not to
react to mouse clicks any more&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Fixed a memory leak in bitmap handling&per. I was using
IBM sample code again&per.&per.&per. 
.br
:li.
XFolder would sometimes attempt to play system sounds
even though no system sounds were enabled&per. Fixed&per.

.br
:li.
XFolder sometimes conflicted with the WPS container
manipulation when extended sorting was on&per. Icons
could still be moved within a folder even though "Always
sort" was on&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Install script failed to create the new "Workplace Shell"
and "OS/2 Kernel" objects when the config folder already
existed&per. Fixed&per. There are now two additional
scripts in \INSTALL&per. 
:eul.:hp2.
:p.
Version 0&per.80 (September 29, 1998):ehp2. XFolder's licence
agreement has changed&per. I am now releasing the source
code and have placed XFolder under the GNU Public Licence&per.
See :link reftype=hd res=10001."Licence":elink. for details&per. 
:p.
New features&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
XFolder can now replace some WPS confirmation dialogs&per.

.br
:li.
Under OS/2 Warp 4, XFolder finally manages to modify
folder menu bars also according to the context menu
settings&per. 
.br
:li.
The :link reftype=hd res=10069.XFolder Startup:elink. folder now has a new menu item in
its context menu&colon. "Start folder content" allows
you to start all the objects in it even after the WPS
is up&per. 
.br
:li.
:link reftype=hd res=10052."QuickOpen":elink. feature for folders&per. 
.br
:li.
The "System" object is now split into two new "OS/2
Kernel" and "Workplace Shell" objects&per. Refer to
:link reftype=hd res=10082.this page:elink. for more&per. 
.br
:li.
New settings pages therein to change those risky and
obscure :font facename='Courier' size=18x12.CONFIG&per.SYS:font facename=default size=0x0. settings&per. Included :link reftype=hd res=10082.plenty
of information:elink. for this&per. 
.br
:li.
New "WPS classes" page for manipulating the WPS class
list&per. 
.br
:li.
Every object now has an "Internals" page in its settings
notebook&per. Here you can look at lots of information
which you can't see otherwise and even change the object's
ID&per. 
.br
:li.
:link reftype=hd res=10047."Copy filename":elink. finally works properly with multiple
selections in a folder&per. Multiple filenames are then
separated by spaces&per. Also introduced new :link reftype=hd res=10053.folder
hotkeys:elink. for copying the filename (without path&colon.
Ctrl+Insert per default)&per. 
.br
:li.
Status bars now support different information in single-object
mode depending on the class to which the selected object
belongs&per. To implement this, I had to introduce even
more WPS class replacements&per. 8-) Moreover, the "$x"
key for status bars now supports formatting text from
the right or as a percentage of the status bar width&per.
Also introduced a few more keys&per. See :link reftype=hd res=10057."Configuring
status bars":elink. for details&per. 
.br
:li.
Status bars now also work for tree views, if you enable
this in the Global Settings&per. 
.br
:li.
Status bars now display the folder's context menu when
you right-click on them&per. 
.br
:li.
Added a new status bar display style ("Warp 3 sunken")&per.

.br
:li.
XShutdown can now display a little animation&per. 
.br
:li.
"Restart Desktop" now has a setting for whether the
startup folder should be processed after the restart&per.

.br
:li.
I have provided a source-code plug-in interface for
people who are willing and able to teach XShutdown how
to do an APM V1&per.2 power-off&per. My BIOS does not
support this, so I cannot do this myself&per. Hopefully
somebody will succeed&per. 
.br
:li.
XShutdown :link reftype=hd res=10070.command-line interface&per.:elink. 
:eul.
:p.
Miscellaneous changes&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
Rearranged the "Context menu" settings pages more logically
(I hope)&per. 
.br
:li.
Finally included proper (and updated) NetscDDE documentation
in a separate INF file&per. NETSCDDE&per.TXT is gone&per.

.br
:li.
Beautified XFolder message boxes a little&per. These
now accept fonts from the font palettes, and these are
stored&per. So at least the XFolder message boxes don't
use that ugly "System Proportional" font any more&per.

.br
:li.
When "Always maintain sort order" is enabled globally,
XFolder now wants a confirmation for whether the Desktop
should also be sorted&per. This will prevent you from
accidentally sorting the Desktop&per. 
.br
:li.
"Show icons" for the "Folder content" functions is now
disabled per default&per. Some video drivers apparently
had serious trouble with this (I was told this for the
Matrox Millenium; my ELSA card works fine though)&per.

.br
:li.
"Folder content" menus are now repositioned on the screen
when they're very large to avoid having them displayed
outside the visible screen area&per. 
.br
:li.
Completely reworked the config folder menu item handling&per.
Previous versions had problems when the &per.LONGNAME
EAs contained different information than the actual
folder content in the INI files&per. These two sources
are now compared and balanced&per. As a side effect,
processing these menu items also now consumes less memory
and is faster&per. 
.br
:li.
Also reworked the folder content menu item handling&per.
Previous versions sent far too many PM messages to the
menu window, which cost a lot of time, especially for
folders on FAT drives, which are not sorted by default&per.
Sorting is now done in memory before inserting the menu
items using a QuickSort algorithm&per. Even on huge
directories, this never takes longer than half a second&per.
I can't do much about the slow icon retrieval though,
that's WPS-internal&per. 
.br
:li.
Since I was given a VisualAge C++ compiler by Mark Mellin
(thanks again), this version is now using a better compiler&per.
Since VisualAge C++ does contain pretty good programming
information, I've spent a couple of days on compiler
options and code optimizing, and I hope that this has
resulted in speedier code&per. 
.br
:li.
Better memory handling altogher&per. XFolder now returns
unused memory to the operating system from time to time&per.

.br
:li.
Replaced my own string handling routines with those
from an old programmers CD-ROM which are way faster&per.

.br
:li.
Converted a few SOM instance methods into regular C
functions&per. This should speed up XFolder a little
bit&per. 
.br
:li.
XShutdown now always closes the Desktop and WarpCenter
windows last&per. This will prevent the situation that
you'll be unable to use your system after Shutdown has
been cancelled because the Desktop has already been
closed&per. 
:eul.
:p.
Yet more bugfixes in this version&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
Moving Object Desktop's TSEnhFolder in the install script
didn't work&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Win95 keys are finally working&per. This time I'm sure
;-) because Glauco Ippolitoni, Italy, sent me a keyboard
with those keys&per. Thanks again&per. 
.br
:li.
Previous versions crashed building the context menus
if the config folder contained a broken shadow&per.
Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
The same applied to folder content menus if broken shadows
were found&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Included much more error checking for those folder content
menus&per. Maybe this solves some of the video driver
problems mentioned above&per. 
.br
:li.
Setting extended sort options from context menus didn't
work for open drive (root folder) views&per. Fixed&per.
But to do this, I had to introduce two new WPS methods&per.
&colon.-( 
.br
:li.
Previous versions kept causing exceptions internally
when objects were being deleted&per. For some reason
which I still don't understand, XFolder's wpUnInitData
method kept getting called twice by the WPS, which really
doesn't make sense&per. Although this error was handled
by the internal WPS exception handler, this slowed down
the deleting process immensely&per. Fixed&per. (But
I'm still amazed&per.) 
.br
:li.
XFolder failed to release an instance mutex semaphore
when a folder was put back to sleep&per. Ooops&per.
Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Found a memory leak in the code doing the "program object
tricks" in the config folder&per. This must have been
in there since XFolder 0&per.3x&per. To my excuse, I
took exactly the example code from the wpQueryProgDetails
Toolkit docs, which also forgets to release the allocated
memory&per. ;-) Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
The values for the "Snap to grid" feature were not dynamically
updated when changed in the Global Settings&per. This
must have broken in V0&per.70&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
"Select by name" appeared in the wrong places when the
"Display" menu was removed&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Folder status bars messed up window painting when the
window was resized so that the status bar overlapped
the title bar, especially when "roll-up" features by,
say, X&per.it were used&per. A simple WS_CLIPSIBLINGS
fixed this&per. 
.br
:li.
"Refresh now" did not refresh status bar data&per. Fixed&per.

.br
:li.
Included more consistency checking for the Worker thread
when it remembers awake objects&per. Previous versions
had a tendency to crash in the Worker thread from time
to time when the Worker thread tried to store an awake
object which wasn't really awake any more&per. (This
occured mainly when deleting many objects in subfolders&per.
For all programmers&colon. contrary to what IBM says
in the SOM documentation, somIsObj obviously is NOT
crash-safe&per.) Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Previous versions opened the objects in the startup
/ shutdown folders from the (background) Worker thread,
which led to sporadic, unpredictable crashes&per. Besides
the WarpCenter strongly disliked not being started from
the Workplace thread&per. These objects are now opened
from the main WPS (Workplace) thread&per. 
.br
:li.
XFolder Startup folder was not processed during first
startup after installation&per. (But only this one time&per.)
Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
The "XFolder Internals" settings page crashed when the
filenames of the NLS DLLs were in capital letters (esp&per.
on FAT drives)&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
XShutdown hung when it tried to close a PM program which
was hung also&per. (Especially with Netscape&per.&per.&per.)
The "Skip" button wouldn't help anymore then, because
it just didn't react&per. Fixed&colon. Messages are
now posted, not sent, to PM windows&per. 
.br
:li.
Contrary to what the "Auto-close non-PM sessions" window
said, no Ctrl+C signal was sent to a non-PM session,
but Ctrl+Break instead&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
The XShutdown Update thread got lost sometimes when
shutdown was initialized&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Completely reworked the XShutdown routines dealing with
saving the INI files&per. Included a lot more error
checking, and the error messages are now more meaningful&per.
I hope that the errors many users have reported have
now disappeared, and if not, they won't take the whole
system down or even crash your WPS&per. 
.br
:li.
Fixed a bug which caused saving the INI files to crash
when they were specified in lower case in :font facename='Courier' size=18x12.CONFIG&per.SYS:font facename=default size=0x0.&per.

.br
:li.
"Paste" and "View" were still called "Insert" and "Display"
in some places&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
A few links in the INF files were messed up&per. Fixed&per.

:eul.:hp2.
:p.
Version 0&per.71 (July 2, 1998):ehp2. Only bugfixes in this
version&per. 
:p.
Bugfixes&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
Status bars were not updated any more when objects were
deleted from an open folder&per. For some reason, the
WPS considers a folder "not populated" any more when
it deletes an object from it, and XFolder therefore
stopped updating status bars&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
V0&per.70 removed the whole "Sort" menu and re-inserted
items with different menu ids even for default WPS sort
menus, which caused other WPS enhancers (X&per.it) to
fail when they were trying to sort folders&per. XFolder
now only ADDS items and leaves the other items alone&per.

.br
:li.
Use of $S keys in "single-object mode" caused other
object information to be always related to last object
in folder (e&per.g&per. "$C objects, $SK KB (selected&colon.
$t [$w] $D $T)")&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Forgot to document a few status bar mnemonics in the
online help&per. 
.br
:li.
Win95 keys were recognized as hotkeys in the Global
Settings, but not saved&per. Again, I don't have those
keys, but I've fixed something&per. Let's see if it
works&per. 
.br
:li.
XFolder sometimes crashed at bootup when no config folder
was present&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Since the WPS crashes big time when menu IDs > 0x8000
are used, XFolder now checks for this (folder content
menus) and aborts processing then&per. 
.br
:li.
The Warp 4 "Insert" menu item is actually called "Paste"&per.
Sorry, I have a German OS/2&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
"Restart Desktop" now saves and closes all open WPS
windows, including the Desktop, regardless of whether
"Close all open windows" was checked&per. Since all
WPS windows will be closed anyway when the WPS terminates,
I might just as well do it myself&per. This has the
advantage that icon positions are finally saved for
the Desktop too&per. 
.br
:li.
"Restart Desktop" doesn't use WPSRESET&per.EXE any more&per.
A simple DosExit(EXIT_PROCESS, 0) does it too&per. If
I had figured this out earlier, this could have saved
me a couple of days of trial and error&per. ;-) 
.br
:li.
Moved a lot of code from the subclassed frame window
procedure to a new, separate object window, which is
also running in the PMSHELL Workplace thread&per. This
might increase compatibility with other WPS software
which also does subclassing&per. 
.br
:li.
Just a cosmetic correction&colon. the "reboot" drop-down
list box in the XShutdown confirmation dialog was disabled
illogically&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Not really a bugfix, but XFolder now creates a shutdown
log in the root directory of your boot drive ("xshutdwn&per.log")&per.
Some people still have trouble getting XShutdown to
work, and this might help tracking these problems down&per.

.br
:li.
Now that I had the shutdown log, I was able to track
down the mysterious problems WRT closing VIO sessions,
and I found a major bug which caused XShutdown to sometimes
close a different session than the one that was intended&per.
Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
I also rearranged the order of commands that were executed
while saving the INIs during shutdown&per. Maybe this
helps those people who (mysteriously) still can't get
those functions to work&per.&per.&per. otherwise, check
the shutdown log&per. 
.br
:li.
Rearranged the order of classes in the install script&per.
Some systems seemed to have problems with the previous
order&per. 
:eul.:hp2.
:p.
Version 0&per.70 (beta) (June 26, 1998):ehp2. Hoo-yah, yet
another mega-release&per. 
:p.
New features&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
:link reftype=hd res=10044."Folder content" functions:elink.&per. 
.br
:li.
:link reftype=hd res=10045."Select by name" function:elink.&per. 
.br
:li.
:link reftype=hd res=10050.Sort extensions&per.:elink.&per. 
.br
:li.
:link reftype=hd res=10056.Folder status bars:elink.&per. 
.br
:li.
:link reftype=hd res=10069.Startup / Shutdown folders:elink.&per. 
.br
:li.
:link reftype=hd res=10090.Sounds!!:elink. 
.br
:li.
Rearranged Global Settings more orderly&per. 
.br
:li.
Cleaned up internal menu handling routines big time
in order to make the new folder content features work&per.
As a result, the 50-objects limit of previous versions
has been removed&per. 
.br
:li.
Default menu items are now removed if a respective checkbox
is :hp1.un:ehp1.checked; this seems more consistent to me&per.

.br
:li.
"Help" submenu may now also be removed&per. 
.br
:li.
XFolder setup strings introduced for use with REXX&per.

.br
:li.
In Icon views, objects are now created from templates
at the mouse position (from where the context menu was
opened)&per. 
.br
:li.
Support for Win95 keyboards (folder hotkeys)&per. 
.br
:li.
Beautified dialogs a little&per. ;-) 
.br
:li.
XShutdown now checks for existing printer queues before
shutting down&per. 
.br
:li.
"Restart Desktop" now remembers whether to close windows
between restarts (checkbox in confirmation window)&per.

.br
:li.
User-configurable reboot actions&per. 
.br
:li.
"Shutdown" and "Restart Desktop" items in Desktop context
menu now contain "&per.&per.&per." only when confirmations
are enabled&per. 
:eul.
:p.
Still more bugfixes&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
Improved exception handling again&per. 
.br
:li.
XFolder refused to create objects altogether when "Open
settings after creating from templates" in the Global
Settings was disabled&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
XFolder crashed when objects were added to the config
folder while these were closed&per. This resulted in
folder context menus not appearing at all&per. Fixed&per.

.br
:li.
XFolder got confused on the "XFolder" page in folder
settings notebooks enabling the checkboxes properly&per.
Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
For mysterious reasons, XFolder would crash on some
systems after dropping something on the root folder
of the boot drive&per. Fixed (I hope)&per. 
.br
:li.
Disabling folder hotkeys would disable all folder subclassing,
including "Auto-scroll tree views"&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
The Warp 4 "View" menu was dubbed "Display" in XFolder
dialogs and help files&per. Sorry, I don't have an English
Warp 4&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
XShutdown failed to save INIs when the existing OS2*&per.INI
files had the HRS attributes on ("An error occured saving
the INI files&colon. 5")&per. This should be fixed now&per.

.br
:li.
XShutdown would sometimes hang after closing all windows,
waiting forever for the Update thread to terminate&per.
Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
XShutdown would sometimes fail to begin shutdown, although
the status window was already displayed, because it
was resetting some event semaphore which was already
posted&per. Fixed&per. 
:eul.:hp2.
:p.
Version 0&per.61 (beta) (May 10, 1998):ehp2. This is mainly
a maintenance release to fix the bugs detected in the
last version&per. 
:p.
Some new features anyway&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
XFolder now populates the Config folders in the background
after Desktop startup, so you don't have to wait forever
on the first right mouse-click&per. 
.br
:li.
New "Auto-close non-PM sessions" setting for XShutdown&per.
By popular demand&per. ;-) 
.br
:li.
New NETSCDDE included&per. See NETSCDDE&per.TXT for
details&per. 
.br
:li.
Changed the default folder hotkey configuration for
more :link reftype=hd res=10053.default hotkeys:elink.&per. 
.br
:li.
Documented :link reftype=hd res=10128.XShutdown internals:elink.&per. 
:eul.
:p.
Even more bugfixes&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
XShutdown failed to save data of folders which were
awake (i&per.e&per. stored somewhere in the WPS process),
although they were not visibly open&per. This applied
especially to the XFolder Config Folder&per. This is
now fixed; all awake folders are saved too&per. 
.br
:li.
XShutdown sometimes failed to save INI files properly&per.
Error checking is now implemented&per. 
.br
:li.
XShutdown sometimes failed to close non-PM sessions&per.
At least DOS/Win-OS/2 sessions had to be closed manually&per.
This was due to a bug (feature?!?) in WinQueryWindowProcess,
which does not return the process and session IDs of
DOS machines, but those of the first PMSHELL instance&per.
I don't know what this should be good for&per.&per.&per.
anyway, it's fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
XShutdown threads had wrong priority settings, so they
would wait forever when a session had higher priority
settings than them&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
XShutdown also sometimes got confused with its thread
management and would start the same thread twice&per.
Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Fixed some minor annoyments in the install script&per.

.br
:li.
Somehow languages got messed up after installation;
the dialogs were in German, the help files in English&per.
Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
"Auto-scroll Tree views" did not always realize when
the WPS was done populating a folder&per. Fixed&per.

.br
:li.
Exception management enhanced&per. Crashes in XFolder
will now not always take the whole WPS down&per. Changed
location of trap log file to the OS/2 boot drive; if
you hear funny sounds, look for "?&colon.\XFLDTRAP&per.LOG"
with "?" being your boot drive&per. 
.br
:li.
Individual folder settings were sometimes set to "disabled"
per default&per. This does of course not make sense&per.
Fixed&per. 
:eul.:hp2.
:p.
Version 0&per.60 (beta) (May 4, 1998):ehp2. I know it's been
a while since the last release, but to make up for it,
this is a mega-version&per.&per.&per. 
:p.
New features / Changes&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
XFolder is finally able to :link reftype=hd res=10043.order context menu items:elink.
according to the order which is seen in Name or Details
views of the corresponding config folder&per. This was
a real hassle&per.&per.&per. 
.br
:li.
"Auto-scroll tree views" feature&per. 
.br
:li.
XFolder is now fully multi-threaded ("XFolder Worker
thread")&per. 
.br
:li.
:link reftype=hd res=10068.Extended Shutdown:elink. and "Restart Desktop" features and
new settings page for Desktop&per. 
.br
:li.
:link reftype=hd res=10047."Copy filename":elink. feature&per. 
.br
:li.
Moved the recreation of the default Config folder into
the XFolder code; this is not any more done by the install
script&per. This way, if the config folder gets lost,
you may recreate your default config folder automatically&per.

.br
:li.
XFolder is finally able to process hotkeys for the Desktop
and drive (disk) objects also&per. 
.br
:li.
There is a new setting on page 1 of the XFolder Global
Settings which tells XFolder what to do after :link reftype=hd res=10041.creating
an object from a template&per.:elink. 
.br
:li.
"XFolder" settings page in every folder&per. 
.br
:li.
XFolder now also replaces the WPObject class in order
to be able to suppress menu items for all Desktop objects&per.
Moreover, "Check disk" and "Format disk" can be removed
from WPDisk objects&per. :link reftype=hd res=10083.Settings:elink. page 2 has been redesigned
for all this&per. 
.br
:li.
My "Netscape DDE Interface" is now included in this
package&per. See :link reftype=hd res=10017."Related files":elink. for more&per. 
.br
:li.
Added "Close window" to the configurable hotkey items
list&per. (Some people seem to prefer "Alt+X" over "Alt+F4"
to close windows&per.) 
.br
:li.
:link reftype=hd res=10017.REPCLASS&per.EXE:elink. now explains itself when started without
parameters&per. 
.br
:li.
:link reftype=hd res=10017.WPSRESET&per.EXE:elink. rewritten&per. 
.br
:li.
Rearranged buttons in all messages boxes to conform
with the OS/2 look and feel&per. 
:eul.
:p.
Bugfixes&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
"Full path in window title" is now ALWAYS properly updated,
even when you move parent folders of an open folder&per.
Thanks to multithreading! 
.br
:li.
Several users have reported problems when Object Desktop
was installed and "unusual" folders (such as workarea
folders and URL folders) were opened&per. This would
completely mess up the WPS, unless folder hotkeys were
disabled&per. This problem should be fixed now, because
I've finally implemented a proper way of remembering
window procedures for each folder window separately&per.
The old code was just awful, sorry&per. 
.br
:li.
I know I've claimed before that this one was fixed,
but when passing directory names to programs as a parameter,
XFolder still forgot to enclose them in quotes when
they contain spaces&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
XFolder was previously unable to differentiate between
"Alt" and "Ctrl" hotkeys&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
:link reftype=hd res=10017.NEWOBJ&per.CMD:elink. can now handle titles with spaces also&per.
Thanks, John Buckley&per. 
:eul.:hp2.
:p.
Version 0&per.52 (March 1, 1998):ehp2. New features&colon.

:ul compact.:li.
Many more configurable items for :link reftype=hd res=10053.folder hotkeys:elink., including
sorting, NPS WPS's "Sort by extension" and OS/2 Warp
4 items&per. 
.br
:li.
XFolder is now prepared for :link reftype=hd res=10039.National Language Support:elink.&per.
It shouldn't take too long before more than just the
English version is available&per. I am planning to distribute
National Language Support files in separate packages&per.
NLS support is now on page 5 of the Global Settings,
to where I also moved two settings which were formerly
on page 1&per. Please :link reftype=hd res=10025.contact the developer's team:elink. if
you're interested in translating XWorkplace to your
language&per. You don't have to be a programmer, but
knowing HTML would help&per. 
.br
:li.
A few renovations on the settings pages&colon. most
importantly, settings which don't apply are now grayed
out&per. 
:eul.
:p.
Even more bugfixes&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
Sometimes hotkeys got activated even though the Ctrl
or Alt keys were not pressed&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
When the folder name was passed to a started program
as a parameter which was started from a WPDisk object,
only the drive letter was passed (e&per.g&per. "C&colon."
instead of "C&colon.\")&per. Fixed&per. 
.br
:li.
Previous versions had problems replacing the default
icon for closed icons, but only on Warp 4&per. Apparently,
on Warp 4, IBM has decided to have wpclsQueryIconData
call BEFORE wpclsInitData, which is really not the way
it should be and, even worse, contradictory to what
IBM recommends in the Toolkit Docs&per. Anyway, this
is fixed now&per. 
.br
:li.
Not really a bugfix, but the hotkey list now uses less
space in OS2&per.INI&per. 
.br
:li.
No bugfix either, but the annoying "No settings found"
message box after opening the settings notebook was
removed&per. 
.br
:li.
I forgot to implement "Remove default menu items" and
help for disk objects also&per. Fixed&per. 
:eul.:hp2.
:p.
Version 0&per.51 (Feb 20, 1998):ehp2. New features&colon.

:ul compact.:li.
Insert separators into menus&colon. simply set a program
object's title to "---"&per. 
.br
:li.
"Refresh now" also updates the window title (if "Full
path in window titles" is enabled)&per. 
.br
:li.
At last, XFolder enhances Drive objects also (i&per.e&per.
the root drive views that can be opened from the "Drives"
folder)&per. Hotkeys still DO NOT work in here&per.

.br
:li.
Added a few more items to the configurable hotkey list&per.

.br
:li.
Two more REXX scripts for folder settings&per. 
:eul.
:p.
Bugfixes (this is a long list, but I believe nothing
of this was really serious)&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
Somehow in the last compile of V0&per.50 the help panels
for the "System" notebook pages got messed up&per. Fixed&per.

.br
:li.
Cleaned up internal menu handling routines&per. Removed
a few weirdos&per. 
.br
:li.
The hotkey entry field in the Settings now only works
when a list box entry has been selected&per. Anything
else didn't make much sense&per. 
.br
:li.
When the settings were re-read from OS2&per.INI at startup,
not all the keyboard hotkeys were initialized, so some
of the definitions got lost at every reboot&per. Fixed&per.

.br
:li.
For some reason, in the last beta, you could add up
to 20 hotkeys, but you could not get rid of them any
more&per. I simply forgot to add a "Clear" button, which
is available now&per. 
.br
:li.
The "full path in folder title" was not updated when
the folder was moved or renamed&per. This now works
half way&per. 
.br
:li.
Removed annoying "XFolder could not query its module
handle" message, which was titled a "fatal error", but
caused no harm in any way&per. 
.br
:li.
Changed default "menu ID offset" setting to 300 to avoid
conflicts with LAN Server and ObjectDesktop from the
start&per. 
.br
:li.
Install program now backs up the original XFolder Configuration
Folder before erasing it and building a new one from
scratch&per. This avoids having duplicate entries in
the XFolder menus after several installs&per. 
.br
:li.
The missing "TREEFONT" setup string has been added to
the :link reftype=hd res=10146."WPFolder Setup Strings":elink. page&per. 
.br
:li.
One more thing&colon. somehow I got the terminology
for "conditional cascade" menus messed up&per. The description
on the first settings page has been corrected&per. 
:eul.:hp2.
:p.
Version 0&per.50 beta (Feb 10, 1998):ehp2. New features&colon.

:ul compact.:li.
:link reftype=hd res=10046."Snap to grid":elink. feature&per. 
.br
:li.
:link reftype=hd res=10053.Folder hotkeys&per.:elink. 
.br
:li.
Moved all the XFolder Global Settings onto four pages
in the OS/2 "System" object in the System Setup folder&per.
I thought that since there are a number of settings
for folders there, I might just as well add XFolder's
settings in that place also&per. 
:eul.:hp2.
:p.
Version 0&per.41 (Feb 8, 1998):ehp2. New features&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
Templates support! Make shadows of your favorite templates
in the configuration folders, and XFolder will create
objects from them&per. 
.br
:li.
Clipboard support via "%**C" in program object parameters&per.

.br
:li.
"Keep original title" setting when displaying full path
in folder window title&per. 
.br
:li.
XFolder menu ID's are now configurable in the Global
Settings&per. 
.br
:li.
Added object id's and object setup strings to documentation&per.

:eul.:hp2.
:p.
Version 0&per.40 beta (Feb 6, 1998):ehp2. Gee, XFolder is
finally getting somewhere&per. New features&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
XFolder Global Settings dialog with zillions of settings&per.
Take a look at it, it's completely new&per. In this
dialog, you can now configure certain aspects of XFolder
that some users found annoying&per. Most importantly,
you can now switch off XFolder's icon replacement&per.

.br
:li.
XFolder can now display the full path of the folder
in the folder window title (e&per.g&per. "C&colon.\OS2\APPS"
instead of just "APPS"), which is a bit more informative&per.

.br
:li.
XFolder can now also remove OS/2 default menu entries&per.

:eul.:hp2.
:p.
Version 0&per.31 (Feb 1, 1998):ehp2. New features&colon. 
:ul compact.:li.
"Create another" objects in the default configuration
now ask for a name before creating&per. 
.br
:li.
More robust online help&per. Meaningful error messages
if not found&per. 
.br
:li.
Added online help for pressing F1 over an XFolder variable
menu item&per. 
:eul.
:p.
Bugfixes -- I told you, 0&per.30 was a beta only ;-)
&colon.
