.* Source file: "xices_4wpsmenuids.html"
:h2 res=10147 x=right width=70%.WPS Menu IDs
:p.
When using the WPObject setup string :font facename='Courier' size=18x12.MENUITEMSELECTED:font facename=default size=0x0.,
the following menu IDs might be useful to you&per. Please
keep in mind that not all of these are intended for
all kinds of objects; for example, "Format disk" does
not make sense on folders, and I don't know what will
happen if you try this out&per. If you're lucky, nothing
happens&per. 
:p.
Note that the new menu items introduced by XWorkplace
have no :hp1.fixed:ehp1. menu IDs, so they're not listed here&per.
Instead, the XWorkplace menu items have :hp1.variable:ehp1. menu
IDs, whose base is specified with the "XWorkplace menu
item ID offset" global setting&per. This base is added
to :font facename='Courier' size=18x12.WPMENUID_USER:font facename=default size=0x0., which is 0x6500 (25856 decimal), and
the XWorkplace menu ID's are then added to that base
to allow compatibility with other WPS enhancers&per.
So if you wish to use an XWorkplace menu item with :font facename='Courier' size=18x12.MENUITEMSELECTED:font facename=default size=0x0.,
you need some utility such as :font facename='Courier' size=18x12.XRAY:font facename=default size=0x0. to figure out the
"real" menu id&per. The ID will of course change again
if you change the offset setting&per. 
:p.
