:h2 res=10148 x=right width=70%.XWorkplace INI Keys
:p.
XWorkplace stores all its global settings in your OS2&per.INI
file&per. (By contrast, the settings for individual
Desktop objects are stored by the WPS, mostly in the
:font facename='Courier' size=18x12.&per.CLASSINFO:font facename=default size=0x0. extended attributes&per.) 
:p.
This section is supposed to explain the keys in the
"XWorkplace" section in OS2&per.INI&per. If you had
XFolder installed previously, XWorkplace copies this
data from the "XFolder" section, which remains in OS2&per.INI
so that you can switch back to XFolder later if you
choose to de-install XWorkplace&per. 
:p.
Note&colon. XWorkplace does not rely on the INI keys&per.
If you really mess up something bad, you can simply
delete a key with an INI editor or the whole "XFolder"
section altogether&per. After the next Desktop restart,
XWorkplace will reinitialize itself with safe default
values&per. 
:p.
Here we go&colon. 
:dl compact break=all.
:dt.:font facename='Courier' size=18x12.Accelerators:font facename=default size=0x0. 
:dd.This has the list of folder hotkeys&per. This data is
binary, and you should not change it manually&per. This
is an array of :font facename='Courier' size=18x12.XFLDHOTKEY:font facename=default size=0x0. structures, as defined in
:font facename='Courier' size=18x12.\shared\common&per.h:font facename=default size=0x0. of the XWorkplace sources&per.
:hp2.Defaults&colon.:ehp2. as described on the :link reftype=hd res=10053."Folder hotkeys":elink.
page&per. 
:dt.:font facename='Courier' size=18x12.AutoClose:font facename=default size=0x0. 
:dd.The list of items which are to be closed automatically
by XShutdown&per. Each item on this list is a zero-terminated
string, followed by a ULONG which signifies what to
do with this item&per. Then comes the next item; if
it's 0, the list is terminated&per. 
:dt.:font facename='Courier' size=18x12.BootLogoFile:font facename=default size=0x0. 
:dd.The fully qualified filename of the OS/2 V1&per.3 &per.BMP
file to use for the Desktop start logo, as set by the
"Startup" page in the Desktop's settings notebook&per.
This is a plain zero-terminated string&per. 
:dt.:font facename='Courier' size=18x12.DialogFont:font facename=default size=0x0. 
:dd.The font to use for XWorkplace message boxes&per. This
gets set when you drop a font on one of them&per. :hp2.Default&colon.:ehp2.
9&per.WarpSans, I think&per. 
:dt.:font facename='Courier' size=18x12.FavoriteFolders:font facename=default size=0x0. 
:dd.Well, the list of :link reftype=hd res=10044.favorite folders:elink., as hex object handles
separated by spaces&per. 
:dt.:font facename='Courier' size=18x12.GlobalSettings:font facename=default size=0x0. 
:dd.This is a large array of ULONGs with all kinds of settings,
mostly from the "Workplace Shell" object&per. This corresponds
to the :font facename='Courier' size=18x12.GLOBALSETTINGS:font facename=default size=0x0. structure as defined in :font facename='Courier' size=18x12.\shared\common&per.h:font facename=default size=0x0.
of the XWorkplace sources&per. You better not change
values in here manually, but you can delete this whole
key to reset XWorkplace to safe default values (after
the next Desktop startup)&per. This gets rewritten every
time some global setting is changed in any of the settings
objects&per. 
:dt.:font facename='Courier' size=18x12.JustInstalled:font facename=default size=0x0. 
:dd.This key only exists right after XWorkplace has been
installed and leads to the "Welcome" information of
XWorkplace and the config folder being created&per.
Afterwards, this key is deleted again&per. 
:dt.:font facename='Courier' size=18x12.Language:font facename=default size=0x0. 
:dd.XWorkplace's three-digit language code, from which the
NLS to be loaded is determined&per. This can be set
in "XWorkplace Setup" and :hp2.defaults:ehp2. to "001", if not
found&per. 
:dt.:font facename='Courier' size=18x12.NameClashLastFocus:font facename=default size=0x0. 
:dd.The dialog item ID which last had the focus in the "Object
exists" dialog&per. 
:dt.:font facename='Courier' size=18x12.QuickOpenFolders:font facename=default size=0x0. 
:dd.The list of :link reftype=hd res=10052.quick-open folders:elink., as hex object handles
separated by spaces&per. 
:dt.:font facename='Courier' size=18x12.RebootTo:font facename=default size=0x0. 
:dd.A list of user-reboot items (which appear in the "Reboot"
drop-down box in the XShutdown confirmation dialog)&per.
This is a list of pairs of zero-terminated strings&colon.
the first one describes the item, the second one specifies
the command to execute&per. The list is terminated by
two extra zero bytes&per. 
:dt.:font facename='Courier' size=18x12.SB_*:font facename=default size=0x0. 
:dd.Various status bar settings&per. The names are pretty
self-explanatory, I think&per. If a key is not found,
a :hp2.default:ehp2. is loaded from the NLS DLL&per. 
:dt.:font facename='Courier' size=18x12.SelectSome:font facename=default size=0x0. 
:dd.The last ten file filters entered in the "Select by
name" dialog, each of which is terminated with a null
byte&per. 
:dt.:font facename='Courier' size=18x12.TrashCan&colon.&colon.Drives:font facename=default size=0x0. 
:dd.A binary array of bytes specifying drives support for
the XWorkplace trash can&per. 
:dt.:font facename='Courier' size=18x12.Version:font facename=default size=0x0. 
:dd.The XWorkplace version which is running&per. This is
only set for informational purposes (e&per.g&per. for
other applications which might be interested), but not
read by XWorkplace itself&per. 
:dt.:font facename='Courier' size=18x12.WndPos*:font facename=default size=0x0. 
:dd.Various window positions to make them reappear where
you closed them&per. These entries use a plain SWP structure
each (I don't use WinStoreWindowPos)&per. 
:dt.:font facename='Courier' size=18x12.XFolderPath:font facename=default size=0x0. 
:dd.The main directory of where XWorkplace is installed&per.
This gets set by the install script and is required
by TREESIZE&per.EXE to find the NLS DLL&per. The XWorkplace
core however does not use this key&per. 
:dt.:font facename='Courier' size=18x12.XWPSound&colon.LastDir:font facename=default size=0x0. 
:dd.The "Sound" object replacement remembers the last directory
used with the "Browse" button here&per. 
:dt.:font facename='Courier' size=18x12.XWPSound&colon.Scheme:font facename=default size=0x0. 
:dd.The "Sound" object replacement remembers the current
sound scheme name here&per. 
:edl.
:p.

